title: thai chicken saute
directions: Luau Style:
Take one large pineapple and cut 1 1/2-inch slices from top and bottom of an unpeeled fruit.
Save these pieces.
Use a long, skinny knife to cut around the fruit, 1/2-inch inside the rind.
Loosen fruit at top and bottom and push it out of the rind in one piece.
Cut peeled pineapple into 6 or 8 wedge-shaped pieces.
Reassemble pieces and refill shell. Replace top and bottom pieces.
Serve by removing pineapple top and taking out sections with fork or fingers.

title: milk shake
directions: Pour milk into blender.
Add ice cream.
Next, add flavored syrup.
Blend ingredients. Pour into glass and enjoy.

title: kool aid pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and spoon into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill and serve.

title: western omelet casserole
directions: Layer 1/3 each of frozen potatoes, ham, onions and cheese in bottom of slow cooker. Repeat 2 times. Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in slow cooker. Cover. Cook on low 8 to 9 hours.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and shape into tiny meat balls. Brown in skillet with a small amount of olive oil.
Now add to sauce and simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: crystalized orange pecans(great for holidays)
directions: In a 2 Quart microwave safe bowl.
Put sugar, cinnamon, orange juice in bowl and mix together.
Then add pecans, and stir a little more.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and cook for 6 minutes on 70% power.
Take our of microwave, be careful bowl will be hot.
Stir and place new plastic wrap over bowl and microwave 8-10 more minutes.
Stirring often in these 8-10 minutes.
When done pour onto cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Let cool and dry for a few hours.
If they stick together break apart.
Store in air tight container or plastic bags.
Very good.

title: tasty toast
directions: Turn control to light for slightly brown or turn control to dark for burnt toast.
Push toaster to start.

title: reception chicken salad
directions: Chop or grind chicken.
Add the other ingredients and mix with enough Miracle Whip to hold the mixture together.
You can add chopped fresh parsley for color, but it is optional.
This is great for teas, brunches, luncheons and any kind of reception.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix all spices together.
Knead into bread.
Refrigerate 3 days kneading each day.
On fourth day, shape into rolls, not over 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Bake on broiler rack at 150° to 175° for 10 hours.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: beans and sausage
directions: Wash beans well; place beans, tomatoes, onion, salt and pepper into a large pot and cook until nearly done.
Add sausage and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve with corn bread and rice.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together the day before you are planning to serve it.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon; drain extra fat.
Fry onions in bacon fat until soft; set aside.
Fry ground beef or chuck until browned.
Add all seasonings.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix in beans, bacon and onions.
Place into a large baking dish or two oven to freezer casseroles.
Bake the entire batch in one pan at 325° for 2 hours or less.
Or freeze in smaller casserole dishes and bake as needed.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes and boil in skins until tender.
While potatoes are cooking, boil the eggs and cut all other ingredients very fine.
Peel potatoes and put in a large bowl.
Add vinegar and let stand 15 minutes.
Cube potatoes and combine all ingredients. This is better if you can serve before refrigerating.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream and chilies.
Divide in half. Add chicken and green onions to half and fill tortillas.
Spread other half on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: shrimp creole-microwave
directions: Combine onion, green pepper, celery and margarine in a 3-quart casserole.
Microwave on High until vegetables are tender, 3 to 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and flour, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Mix in remaining ingredients except shrimp. Cover.
Microwave at High until mixture is bubbly, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir in shrimp.
Cover. Microwave on High until shrimp is opaque and tender, 4 to 6 minutes.
(Do not overcook or shrimp will be tough.)
Stir twice during cooking.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Sprinkle a little mustard on chops and brown in oil.
In casserole, arrange potatoes, onions and chops in layers.
Mix the rest of ingredients together and pour over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add milk and egg to dry ingredients; mix. Pour into a greased skillet or pan. Bake at 400° to 450° until brown.

title: walnut stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Combine bread crumbs, half of butter, onion, celery, parsley, walnuts, salt, pepper and enough water to moisten.
Make 4 mounds of stuffing each on a square of foil.
Arrange on small cookie sheet.
Brush both sides of chicken breasts with lemon juice.
Then spoon remaining butter over.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place open chicken breast over each mound.
Shape around stuffing, tucking sides under.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: "khreschatic" cake
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff, slowly adding confectioners sugar and ground nuts.
Divide into 5 equal parts in greased and floured 8 or 9-inch spring-form pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Gently take out of pans and cool.

title: orange delectable cake
directions: Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, salt, yolks and milk, gradually, while cooking on top of a double boiler, stirring gradually until mixture thickens (about 10 minutes).
Set aside to cool.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Chop green pepper and onion; mix with the meat, water and tomatoes in a pan.
Heat to boiling; lower heat and cook slowly 10 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and cook slowly for 25 minutes, until rice is tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Makes six 3/4-cup servings.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Lightly toast coconut on baking sheet.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oleo, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: coconut cake
directions: *For tropical beverages and cooking.
Coco Lopez or other brand nonalcoholic but sold near alcoholic beverages.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: In a heavy-bottomed 2-quart saucepan, heat the cream, milk, sugar and vanilla beans.
(If you are using vanilla extract, do not add it until last.)
Stir occasionally until sugar is dissolved and the mixture is hot but not boiling.
Whisk egg yolks together in a bowl.
Continue whisking and very slowly pour in approximately 1 cup of the cream mixture.
When smooth, pour back into the pan.
Whisk constantly over low heat until the mixture thickens slightly and coats the back of a spoon.
If the line you make remains, the custard is done.
Remove vanilla beans (or if you're using vanilla extract, add it now).
Chill mixture thoroughly.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: elephant balls
directions: Mix together confectioners sugar, margarine and peanut butter, then add Rice Krispies.
Mix by hand and shape into balls.

title: green bean bake
directions: Mix beans, soup and one half of the onion rings
Place in baking dish and top with reserved onion rings.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350 F till top is golden brown.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 10 pan with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken on beef.
Lay 1/2 strips of bacon on each piece of chicken.

title: creamy persimmon fudge
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, except butter.
Cook to very firm ball when dropped into ice water, then add butter.
When cool, beat until it starts to take on a dull appearance.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: beef parmesan
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and pound to 1/4-inch thick.
Dip in egg and roll in mixture of Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Brown steak in oil, then place in baking dish.
Cook onion in same skillet until tender.
Stir in salt, pepper, sugar, oregano, marjoram and tomato paste.
Add hot water.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour most of sauce over steak.
Top with slices of Mozzarella cheese, then rest of sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Add water if needed.
Serve over noodles, spaghetti or rice.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, eggs, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in a large skillet and brown meatballs.
Remove from skillet and pour off fat.

title: schnitzel beans
directions: Dice the bacon; fry until crisp.
Slice onion; fry until soft. Cut the beans into small, 1-inch pieces; brown them slightly with the bacon and onion.
Add the tomatoes, seasonings and boiling water; cover and cook very slowly until beans are tender.
Add more water, if necessary, so there will be a little sauce to serve with the beans.

title: mexican pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add ground beef and cook until brown on medium heat.
Add chili powder, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook until liquid cooks down.
Add rice.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into quarters.
Preheat oven to 400°. Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a mixing bowl, combine 1/3 of potatoes with 1 to 2 tablespoons cooking oil, onion soup mix and spices, if desired.
Spread in baking pan.
Repeat with potatoes, oil, soup mix and spices until all potatoes are coated.
Bake at 400° for approximately 1 hour. Serve with ketchup and/or sour cream, if desired.

title: liqueur
directions: Remove all white from mandarin peel and discard.
Finely chop peel, mix with cinnamon and coriander.
Pour the brandy over this mixture, mix thoroughly.
Store in covered bottle for two months. Filter and bottle.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling salted water.
Stir in butter and garlic cheese.
Put eggs in cup and add milk to make 1 cup, beat.
Add to grits.
Bake in greased 2-quart dish 1 hour at 300°.
Top with grated cheese the last 10 minutes, if desired.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale, and freeze.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale to frozen ingredients.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, Knorr vegetable mix and green onions.
Add spinach to mixture.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased tube pan where chopped nuts have been placed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and cottage cheese cups
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Add mushrooms and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Place cottage cheese and eggs in blender to blend.
Place this in a bowl and add ham with onion and mushrooms with nutmeg and seasoning.
Grease a muffin tin and divide mixture equally between them.
This makes 6 small cups.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake 25 minutes at 400° until brown on top.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, chop and drain.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Layer one-half broccoli, one-half chicken and one-half soup mixture in a lightly greased 2 quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with crumbs and almonds.
May be refrigerated until ready to bake.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple passion cake
directions: Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 inch baking pan.
Mix cake mix and bake according to package directions for 15 minutes; cool.
Mix pudding and milk as directed; stir in softened cream cheese. Spread over cooled cake.
Spread whipped topping over pudding. Sprinkle pineapple evenly over whipped topping.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over pineapple.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over coconut and top with maraschino cherries.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix onions in cream cheese.
Mix 1/2 ham in cream cheese. Shape in a ball and roll in other half of ham.

title: jean's corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Then cream in margarine and add well beaten eggs.
Next blend in the evaporated milk and the can of water.
(Sometimes, I use less water, depending on how soupy the creamed corn is.)
Then stir in the corn and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until set, usually 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut the broccoli in small chunks.
Add onion, bacon and raisins.
Mix the remaining ingredients together for dressing and add to the broccoli mixture.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Pour melted margarine over
sugar
and	stir well.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Mix
well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rhode island clam cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion, egg, oil and drained clams, reserving clam juice.
Using juice as a liquid, add a little at a time until batter is as thick as fritter batter.
Fry until golden in deep fat at 375°, using a mounded tablespoonful of batter per cake.
Salt to taste after draining on paper towels.
May be served with clam or seafood chowder or eaten as a snack.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Drain hominy.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz; mix thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavorings until fluffy. Also food coloring if desired. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a separate bowl. Combine the two mixtures and chill for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Blend butter and sugar.
Beat well until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in apples, Raisin Bran and sifted dry ingredients.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: microwave hamburger stroganoff
directions: Crumble ground beef into microwave-safe casserole.
Add onion and celery.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring once.
Stir to break meat into pieces; drain.
Add mushrooms, noodles, water, bouillon, parsley and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, or until noodles are tender, stirring once or twice, making sure noodles are cooked with liquid to assure tenderness.
Stir in sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first four ingredients together and pour into pan.
Crush crackers on top, then pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake 25 minutes or until bubbling and brown.
Quick, easy and everyone's favorite.

title: lemon cool
directions: Mix well.
Press in bottom (not sides) of dish.
Bake at 325°. Let cool.

title: six layer casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, make a layer of each ingredient.
Season each layer to your taste.
Cover and bake one hour at 325°. Uncover and bake up to one hour or more until vegetables are tender.

title: aunt kathy's "turtle cake"
directions: Mix box cake mix as directed.
Divide in 2 bowls.
To one bowl, add 1/2 can Eagle Brand milk and 2 sticks melted butter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: nellie's beans
directions: In kettle, brown sausage or ham in 1/2 teaspoon of butter. Add shallots.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add potatoes and bacon drippings. Add enough milk to make dough soft.
Roll out on floured board 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place biscuits in greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice with 1 bay leaf.
When done, remove bay leaf and set aside.
Saute onion in the butter until clear; remove from heat. Fold in rice and sour cream.
In a separate bowl, combine grated cheese, cottage cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
In baking dish, layer 1/2 rice mixture, 1/2 green chilies, then 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: country fried corn
directions: Heat oil on medium heat in a large skillet.
Pour flour, salt and pepper into a medium bowl, and toss to mix seasonings.
Add drained corn and toss with a fork to thoroughly coat corn.
Add to skillet.
Add butter to corn and stir every couple of minutes until golden brown.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool.
Add ginger ale. Chill.
When slightly thickened, add vinegar, pineapple and carrots.
Turn into mold.
Chill until firm.
Eat plain or serve with salad dressing.

title: watermelon frappe
directions: Remove seeds and rind.
Cut melon into chunks.
Combine melon, limeade and ginger ale in blender.
Freeze for several hours. Thaw partially to serve.
Spoon into glasses and garnish with lime or lemon slices.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: dad's famous italian potato salad(aka:  potato salad to die for)
directions: Cook scrubbed potatoes in lightly salted water until done. Drain and cook until you can handle them.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook whole zucchini in boiling salted water about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers leaving 1/4-inch thick shell.
Chop zucchini meat.
Saute garlic, onions and parsley in margarine in large skillet.
Add mushrooms; cook until tender.
Stir in flour and oregano.
Stir in shredded cheese, pimento and chopped zucchini.
Heat through.

title: browned rice
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake covered about 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Place flour, sugar, salt and shortening in bowl.
Mix with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl beat egg, water and vinegar and combine with flour mixture until moist.
Divide dough into 5 parts for 2 1/2 pies.
May be made ahead and frozen until ready for use. You can freeze up to 3 weeks.

title: coffee cake
directions: Melt margarine in Bundt pan, then pour into bowl.
Mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Dip biscuits in margarine then roll in sugar mixture.
Stand on end in pan to make a round cake. Pour any leftover margarine over cake and sprinkle over remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Butter 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan. Stir in saucepan, evaporated milk, sugar and salt; cook over low heat until mixture boils. Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add and stir until melted marshmallows and chocolate morsels.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Turn into pan.
Refrigerate.
Makes 36 squares. Never fail; super easy.

title: kahlua kake
directions: Lightly grease Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients by hand and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan. Powdered sugar can be sprinkled or sifted over the top before serving.

title: stir-fried ginger and orange broccoli
directions: Coat the bottom of a saut pan or wok with vegetable oil or cooking spray. Heat the pan over high heat until it begins to lightly smoke. Add the broccoli and stir-fry until heated through. Add the scallions, garlic, ginger and orange zest. Stir-fry another minute and serve immediately. Serves 4 to 6 people as a side dish.

title: fruit salad sauce
directions: Melt butter and add vinegar.
Mix in beaten eggs and cream. In separate bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt and dry mustard.
Add egg mixture to dry mixture slowly.
Add butter and vinegar.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Add Cool Whip before serving.
Blend into assorted fresh fruit pieces.
May store sauce in refrigerator up to one month.

title: julia smith's chili
directions: Cook meat and chopped vegetables until meat is no longer red. Stir in Chili-O mix until dissolved.
Add tomato sauce and water. Cook on stove for about 30 minutes.
Stir to prevent sticking. Remove to crock-pot and simmer for about 2 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Add to buttermilk.
Add mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn on board or pastry cloth.
Roll or pat to desired thickness.
Cut biscuits.
Dip in melted butter.
Place on greased pans.
Bake at 540° for 12 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put sliced apples in greased baking dish.
Mix ingredients and crumbs over apples.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: picnic beans
directions: In mixing bowl mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: steak etouffee
directions: Put olive oil in a large pot on medium heat.
Saute onions, pimientos, parsley and celery seed until onions are clear.
Add mushroom steak sauce, wine, soy sauce, bitters and hot sauce.
Add garlic after mixture is juicy.
Turn fire down and add meat. Cover and let cook 3 to 4 hours until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: nachos supremos
directions: Crumble beef and chorizo into a large skillet.
Add onions and cook until meat is browned; drain and add several drops of hot pepper sauce.
Spread beans in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle with green onions, chiles and cheeses. Drizzle salsa over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with guacamole and sour cream.
Garnish with black olives.
Tuck tortilla chips around edges and serve.
Good hot or cold.
Serves 12.

title: favorite banana bread
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and margarine, mixing until well blended.
Blend in bananas and eggs.
Add combined remaining ingredients, mixing just until moistened.

title: turtles
directions: Unwrap the Milky Ways and roughly chop. Melt in top of a double boiler along with condensed milk and butter. Blend until smooth. Remove from heat and add nuts. Refrigerate for 20 minutes. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Freeze for 15 minutes. Melt almond bark. Using a fork, dip the turtles in the chocolate, one at a time. Place turtles on wax paper and freeze until firm. Keep refrigerated.

title: green chili (mexican stew)(warning!  not for the weak.)
directions: Combine ingredients and add water to cover and pork gravy (may be gravy mix).
Simmer (the longer you simmer it the better it will be).
May add more or less ingredients depending on how hot you like it.

title: strawberry yogurt-cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Stir in yogurt, honey and vanilla. In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup of water; let stand for 1 minute. Stir over low heat to dissolve gelatin. Stir gelatin mixture and remaining 1/2 cup of water into cream cheese mixture. Fold in 1/2 cup of sliced strawberries. Fill crust with cheese mixture. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Cut onion into wedges.
Cut green pepper into strips.
Finely chop garlic.
Melt margarine in a skillet on medium high.
Saute onion, lemon pepper and garlic 3 minutes; add remaining scampi ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add fettuccini; toss and heat thoroughly.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Bring to rapid boil 3 quarts water and 1 tablespoon salt. Gradually add macaroni.
Boil until macaroni is tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Brown onion in skillet.
Add diced celery and ground beef.
Brown slowly.
Add salt, pepper and tomatoes. Mix well and fold in macaroni.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.	Top with crushed potato chips.
Return to oven and bake uncovered 15 minutes.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Form a well in center and mix rest of ingredients, adding mangos, raisins or nuts last.
Bake in loaf pan about 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked crispy ranch chicken
directions: Combine dressing mix and crushed cornflakes. Roll chicken in mixture. Place in ungreased baking pan. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: jessica's favorite snack
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Cut cheese in strips. Arrange on plate in alternating rows of apples and cheese.
Place crackers in the center of the plate.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Alternate this mixture with streusel.
Grease and flour pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ham hocks and beans
directions: Combine all the ingredients in slow cooker or crock-pot.
Cook all day.
Take skin and fat off ham hocks.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, skim off all the fat.
Heat and serve.

title: rice pudding (kheer)
directions: Bring 6 cups milk to boil in heavy shallow 5-quart saucepan. Rinse rice with cold water.
Drain.
Stir rice into milk.
Reduce heat and simmer until pudding thickens and rice is tender, stirring frequently, for about 1 1/4 hours.
Puree 1/4 cup milk and almonds in blender until smooth; stop frequently to scrape down sides of blender.
Add banana, sugar, cardamom and saffron and blend.
Pour this puree into pudding.
Rinse blender with remaining 1/4 cup milk and add to pudding.
Continue simmering until thickened to consistency of tapioca, about 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, spoon into goblets and sprinkle with pistachios.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all together; refrigerate at least 45 minutes.
Shape and roll into cheese log.
Then roll real good in chopped walnuts. Serve with crackers.

title: rich recipe cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: esther's pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mother's sausage goulash
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter until half soft.
Cut sausage in thin slices, chop tomatoes.
Combine onions and pepper mixture, mushrooms (do not drain), tomatoes (do not drain) and sausage mixture together.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes covered. Serve as a main dish alone or over rice.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, sugar, 1/2 cup melted margarine, 2 eggs and vanilla and mix well.
If mixture seems extra thick, add 1/4 cup milk; if mixture seems thin, add 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Place mixture in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 2 1/2 tablespoons melted margarine and pecans in separate bowl.
Mix thoroughly and sprinkle topping on squash mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot creamed chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in a crock-pot.
Mix water, soup, sour cream and mushrooms.
Add flour.
Mix until well blended.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve chicken and sauce over rice or noodles.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and mash.
Add tomatoes, onion and jalapeno pepper (optional). Add
salt and garlic to taste.
Add lemon juice.

title: orange bundt cake
directions: Blend ingredients for 5 minutes, or until mixture is smooth and fluffy.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: microwaved apples
directions: Place apples, butter, sugar and cinnamon in a glass dish.
Pour a little water in dish.
Microwave for 4 minutes on High.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add wine, cranberry sauce and drained pineapple.
Stir in nuts.
Chill until well set.
Beat cream cheese with sour cream until smooth.
Spread over gelatin. Sprinkle with additional chopped nuts.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Put rhubarb in a bowl; add sugar and all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or until firm.

title: ice pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and salt in ice water for 3 hours.
Drain well. Bring sugar, pickling spices and vinegar to a boil.
Add cucumbers to vinegar mixture and bring to a boil.
Place in jars and seal.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
and
onion;
drain.
Add
taco sauce, peppers
and
soups.
Line	casserole
with chips;	layer with meat
mixture.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Another	can of either soup may be added if needed. You may also substitute corn tortillas for the taco flavored.)

title: sunday waffles
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt together. Combine beaten egg yolks, milk and melted butter; blend thoroughly.
Add liquid mixture all at one time to dry ingredients; mix only until batter is smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites and bake on hot waffle iron.
Makes 8 waffles.

title: cinnamon coffee leaf ring
directions: Let the milk cool, then add the yeast.
Set aside.
Cream together the Crisco, 1/4 cup butter, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add the eggs.
Add the milk-yeast mixture to the butter mix.
Add the flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.

title: chilled zucchini soup
directions: Mix onion, zucchini, chicken broth, water and bouillon; cook for 20 minutes, or until vegetables are soft.
Add remaining ingredients; puree and chill.
Before serving, add milk to desired taste and thickness.
Sprinkle with chives just before serving.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt choc. chips and butter together in a large bowl. Mix in cereal. Mix until cereal is coated well. Then add the sugar. Mix well. Serve.

title: tangy cucumbers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Drain and toss with remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.

title: killer kline's hot wings
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Combine ingredients and stir well.
Add chicken and mix to coat.
Refrigerate.
Stir wings every 30 minutes for one hour while marinating.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30-45 minutes, basting halfway through.
Or, grill over low heat for 30-45 minutes basting every 10 minutes.
Serve with your favorite beverage and ranch dressing.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients. Let set 1 hour. Serve in bowl or on salad greens.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Split bread in half.
Put mustard and butter on each side. Add ham and cheese.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Spread in pie pan the refried beans.
Sprinkle with green chilies. Top with sour cream.
Add chopped ripe olives.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Add salsa.
Top with chopped green onion and chopped tomatoes (optional).

title: chewy chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13 pan with nonstick cooking spray. Cut cookie dough into 1/2 crosswise, cut each section in half lengthwise. With floured fingers, press dough in bottom of pan to for crust. Bake for 10 minutes. Remove crust from oven. In medium bowl, combine milk, peanut butter, vanilla and egg yolks. Mix until smooth. Spoon evenly over partially baked crust. Return to oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes, Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips and let stand for 3 minutes. Then spread chocolate evenly over top. Cool 1 1/2 hours then refrigerate 30 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: green bean salad with honey lime dressing
directions: Cook beans according to package directions until just tender-crisp.
Rinse under cold water and drain.
In small bowl or custard cup combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well together. Chill.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter; press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Press water from spinach. Combine all ingredients. Cover and chill several hours. Good with fresh veggies or crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover beans with cold water overnight.
Drain and rinse. Cover with cold water, add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour (test for doneness by blowing on a spoonful, they should split).
Drain, but save cooking water.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate together and set aside.
Beat eggs until foamy, add sugar and beat until lemon color.
Add remaining ingredients, adding chocolate and butter mixture last.
Beat all together.
Put in a big browning pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: orange slice cake(makes a 5-pound cake)
directions: Combine the butter and sugar; stir in the eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add the orange slices, coconut, dates, pecans and orange peel.
Turn mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 2 hours in a 300° oven.
Allow to cool in pan overnight, setting on a cooling rack.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream in large bowl brown sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Fold in apples and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle top with coconut and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve.
Serves 12.

title: sunny corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Sift together dry ingredients; add egg, milk and shortening. Mix well until smooth. Pour in greased 8-inch square pan or greased muffin pan. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 12 muffins. Half recipe for 6 muffins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie pan. Prepare potatoes as directed on box except decrease water to 1 cup and omit milk.
To this potato mixture, add beaten egg, green onions and sour cream; mix well.
Press potato mixture against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Prick bottom and sides with a fork and bake 15 minutes.

title: orange glazed beets
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, blend in cornstarch and salt.
Add sugar, vinegar and orange juice; cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add beets and simmer over low heat for about 10 minutes until heated through.
Serves six.

title: busy-day beef stew
directions: Mix tomato juice with tapioca.
Pour over meat and vegetables in casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake 4 hours at 250°.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Place pretzels on large cookie sheet and bake for 5 minutes. In a bowl combine oil, garlic powder, dill weed and dressing. Toss warm pretzels into mixture and stir well.
Place back onto cookie sheet and bake for additional 5 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: green pea salad
directions: Place peas, bacon bits and cheese in mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise and stir to coat.

title: golden nuggets
directions: Cool carrots. Combine with onion and pepper.
In a separate bowl, combine other ingredients to taste; stir to dissolve sugar. Pour over carrot mixture and refrigerate 48 hours or more, stirring 2 to 3 times daily to dissolve rest of sugar.
This is a great salad when lettuce is out of season!

title: slob-jerky recipe
directions: Grind your meat and add the remaining ingredients thoroughly in a bowl while kneading the meat like dough.
Let the meat sit in the refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours after mixing to ensure uniform release of flavor throughout the meat.

title: squash and corn casserole
directions: Mix all together thoroughly. Heat in 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder together; cut in butter. Blend egg into a one cup measuring cup, add enough milk to make 1 cup liquid.
Beat egg and milk, add to flour mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Cover with pie filling.

title: fruit trifle(serves 12)
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions, using milk and juice for liquid. Stir in raisins and 3/4 carton whipped topping into the pudding. Measure and drain 1/2 cup pineapple for garnish. Cut cake into chunks.
Place in dish.
Pour pudding and remaining pineapple, fruit salad, etc., over cake.
Add 1/2 cup sherry if desired.

title: cole slaw
directions: Place vegetables in a bowl.
Stir together in a saucepan and cook slowly until slightly thickened the egg, mustard, celery seed, sugar, vinegar and water.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over vegetables.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool and put on topping.

title: fanny farmer bars
directions: Melt cocoa, butter and salt together.
Cool and add flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Take out and cover with tiny marshmallows. Bake for 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: festive shrimp and fettucine
directions: In skillet, heat margarine.
Add shrimp and green pepper with garlic and red pepper.
Stir in soup, water and vinegar.
Heat through.
Serve over fettucine.

title: amazing pie
directions: Mix and pour into 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peppermint strips
directions: Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter or oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix in egg yolk and chocolate bits.
Press mixture into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Beat egg white until frothy; brush over top of dough. Sprinkle with candy.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into strips while warm.

title: coconut cake squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted oleo and 2 eggs.
Makes a stiff batter.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar together and spread
on first
layer.
Sprinkle
each
layer with coconut. Bake 40
to
45 minutes at 325°.
DO NOT open oven door while cooking.

title: brennan's artichoke soup(new orleans, la)
directions: Saute onions in oleo until clear.
Add artichokes; saute a bit longer.
Add soups, water and Kitchen Bouquet.
Simmer until onions are soft.
Add oysters and juice.
Simmer 10 more minutes and serve.

title: amalgamation pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Put all into 3 quarts of hot water, let stand for 30 minutes and drain.
With 1 pint of vinegar and 1 pint of water add 4 tsp. mustard seed, 4 Tbsp. celery seed and drained vegetables.
Boil this for 20 minutes and add 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Makes about 15 small jars.

title: pumpkin angel food cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
Mix pumpkin and spice, fold into cake batter.
Bake as directed on package.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a bowl; mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet with teaspoon; flatten out.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: pizza with hamburger crust
directions: Spread hamburger on pizza pan or small cookie sheet.
Spread spaghetti or pizza sauce on top.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Can also add green peppers, olives, etc.
Bake at 350° until hamburger is brown and cheese is melted.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Stir egg into soups (undiluted).
Add bread.
Add chicken and place in greased casserole dish.
Top with crumbs made with crackers and melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: kj fruit float
directions: Fill tall glass with fruits (raspberries, blueberries, bananas, strawberries, pineapple, etc.)
Pour in chilled ginger ale. Top with 1 scoop of lime sherbet.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions. Add pudding and mix well. When cake is done, punch holes and pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk over cake. Let cool completely. Pour 1 can crushed pineapple over cake and cover with whipped cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the 2 packages of jello in the boiling water.
Let cool, but not congeal.
Stir in the celery, nuts, pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Mix and congeal.

title: toffee bars
directions: Combine oleo, butter and sugar. Simmer on low 4 to 5 minutes. Cover a cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Arrange a layer of graham crackers on the foil. Put chopped pecans on the graham crackers. Cover with butter and sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool and break into pieces.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening, oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients and chopped and floured nuts.
Add bananas.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans (or you may use waxed paper to line pans) in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean. Frost with caramel icing.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into 1/8-inch of hot oil in a large skillet.
Flatten and brown on both sides.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Place in 13x9 pan.
Bake at 400° for 25-30 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Spray Pam on a Bundt pan or grease well (no flour).
Mix the brown sugar, white sugar and cinnamon in Ziploc bag.
Quarter each biscuit from all 4 packages and shake the quarters in the bag with the sugar.
Put the coated wedges all into the Bundt pan.
Pour the leftover sugar mix on top of the wedges then drizzle the stick of melted butter over the top of the entire pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Invert while hot onto cake plate and eat it while it is hot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: For either vegetable, slice enough for a gallon and pour in enough water to just cover the vegetables.
Add 6 tablespoons cider vinegar and 2 1/2 tablespoons salt.
Bring to a boil until vegetables change color.
Pack in hot jars.
Fasten lids and set away until ready to use.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add oil; mix with fork until crumbly.
Stir in milk until ingredients are moistened.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: german upside-down cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, cream cheese and vanilla; set aside.
Mix nuts and coconut next in a greased pan.
Mix cake mix by directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Spoon over icing all over cake mix.
Drop by spoon in big drops.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool before cutting cake.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Add seasonings and spices to vinegar (dilute with 1/3 cup water) and simmer about 8 minutes.
Strain and pour over peeled eggs.
Seal and let stand 2 days before using.
Fill 1 quart jar with 12 to 16 eggs.
(Can add sprig of dill, caraway seed or garlic or onion for different flavors.) Using pickled beet juice with the spices makes a pretty pink for hors d'oeuvres or cold plate.

title: apple or peach strudel
directions: Into bottom of a buttered baking dish put a thick layer of apples or peaches.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixed.
Dot with lumps of butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon into a mixing bowl sift, 1 cup sugar, 1 tsp baking powder, 1 cup flour, 1/2 tsp salt.
Into this sifted mixture, break 1 egg.
Mix until crumble.
Put over fruit.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) till crust is brown.
Serve with milk, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken-sausage-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Stir cooked sausage, soup, Worcestershire and mushrooms into rice.
Spoon half the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with cubed chicken and remaining rice mixture.
Top all with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: Cook macaroni; drain. Brown ground meat and onion; drain off excess fat. Add tomato sauce and spices. Simmer 10 minutes. Beat egg, milk and salt; mix together with macaroni and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with meat mixture, then top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let set for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chocolate wacky cake
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients first and then stir.
Add vinegar, cold water and vanilla; mix well.
Add the oil last and blend well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Prepare the night before serving.
Butter the bread and place, buttered side down, in an 11 x 17-inch Pyrex dish.
Cook sausage and green onions together.
Add to bread.
Mix eggs and milk. Pour over the other ingredients.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Cover with foil and place in refrigerator overnight. Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil the last 10 to 15 minutes.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.
Good with fruit salad and muffins.

title: tootie frootie punch
directions: Mix orange juice and apple juice according to directions on cans.
Pour together in a punch bowl.
Slice oranges (leave peeling on) and let them float on top.
Add Sprite and packages of Kool-Aid (do not add water to Kool-Aid).

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Stir
together the first five ingredients and pour over the hash
browns.
Put
the
mixture
in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish. Top
with the Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Place raisins in boiling water; set aside.
(Drain off water before adding raisins to batter.)
Blend eggs, oil and sugar together.
Add mashed pork and beans.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins.
Add nuts if desired.
Grease and flour 2 standard loaf pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and make into balls.
Brown and drop into your favorite sauce that has started to boil.

title: preserve-filled foldovers
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours.
Roll dough out on a floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon preserves onto center of each square.
Moisten edges of squares; fold pastry in half diagonally, making sure edges are even.
Press edges together with fork or fingers until sealed.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, mushroom soup, mayonnaise and 1/2 cup of cheese; sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix dry yeast in warm water until dissolved.
When milk has cooled, add beaten egg and salt.
Cut shortening into flour and add to mixture.
Knead dough with hands until springy and has a satin-like finish.
Place, covered, in a warm area and let rise until double in bulk or place in refrigerator until next day.
Roll onto 15-inch pizza pan.
Bake partially (10 minutes at 350°); add sauce, spice, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni; cook until done at 400°.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Dice eggplant and boil in salted water for about 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Saute ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain excess grease.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy, then add pumpkin.
Gradually sift in sugar, ginger and cinnamon; chill.
Serve with dried apple chips and gingersnaps.

title: cheddar filled beef rolls
directions: Combine
meat, 1/4 cup of bread crumbs, barbecue sauce, egg and salt.
Mix well.
Pat meat mixture into a 14 x 8-inch rectangle
on
foil.
Combine cheese, balance of bread crumbs, green pepper and water.
Pat cheese mixture on top of the meat mixture.
Roll meat and cheese up from the 8-inch side.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: broiled crab melt-a-ways
directions: Mix all ingredients, except muffins.
Spread equally on muffin halves.
Freeze for at least 30 minutes.
Broil, or freeze and broil later.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 servings.
Great for lunch whole, or cut in quarters and served with cocktails.
These can be frozen for weeks or months, if kept airtight.

title: chocolate sauce for ice cream
directions: Cook all ingredients, except butter and vanilla, until thick. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Let cool or serve warm.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Add water to jello and dissolve.
Then add cinnamon candies until dissolved.
Add applesauce and nut meats.
Refrigerate.

title: blue ribbon carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.

Stir in flour mixture, pineapple, carrots, coconut and chopped pecans. Pour batter into 2 heavily greased and floured 9-inch round pans. Bake at 350 F for 35-40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Immediately pour buttermilk glaze evenly over layers.
Cool in pans 15 minutes, then remove from pans and let cool.

title: ester's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and beat until sugar dissolves.
Pour into container.

title: black as night chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar, baking soda, flour and baking powder.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
Batter should be like water.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix together
flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Cut in butter and
then
add starter.
Mix well, but not too long. Roll out on
floured
surface
and
cut into shape or use your hands. Bake in a hot oven until done.

title: beet salad
directions: Approximately 1 to 2 hours before serving, mix and refrigerate.

title: quick sausage snack(april, 1995)
directions: Trim sandwich bread.
Roll flat with rolling pin.
Spread with horseradish mustard and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add Brown 'N Serve sausage.
Roll up sausage in each slice and secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: carrots vichy
directions: Combine sliced carrots and grated onion.
Slightly cover with water and cook until tender and about half of the water is boiled out.
Stir in remaining ingredients, cooking and stirring until thickened.
This makes an attractive side dish with beef or pork slices.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: mushroom ham canapes
directions: Chop mushrooms, onions, ham and parsley.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add spices.
Add 1 stick of butter; blend and refrigerate.
Spread mixture on thin slice bread.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Combine in mixing bowl with yeast the cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, baking soda and egg.
Stir in flour. Cover and let rise 60 minutes.
Stir down; turn into buttered casserole dish and let rise (approximately 25 minutes).
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt. Serve hot or cooled.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Crust:
Cut shortening into 1 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Add 1 to 3 tablespoons cold water until pastry holds together. Handle as little as possible.
Roll out and place in pie pan.

title: easy cake spicy
directions: Put on stove. Boil 5 minutes; take off heat. Add enough flour to thicken. Add 1 teaspoon baking soda. Mix good and put into greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Put some powdered sugar on top or a cream frosting.

title: oyster pie
directions: Break crackers.
In baking dish, put a layer of crackers and a layer of oysters until all used.
Mix milk, egg, salt and pepper together.
Pour over oysters and crackers.
Dot with butter.
You may have to add a bit more milk to make a little juicier.
Bake at 350° until it begins to brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: To prepare crust, crush pretzels.
Mix pretzels with oleo and sugar. Pat in a 9x13 glass dish to form a crust.
Bake at 400° for 8 mins.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese and 1 c. sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour on top of cooled crust.
Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Allow to set for 10 mins.
Strawberries will thaw.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: squid sauce(salsa di calamiri)
directions: In medium saucepan,
saute
sliced
onion
in olive oil until just tender.
Add
cleaned
and washed squid (see directions) to onions and
saute
until
squid turns red and curls, about 5 minutes.
Remove
squid
from
pan and set aside.
Add tomato puree and water to saucepan.
Stir and heat over medium high heat. Add rest
of ingredients and bring to boil.
Lower heat to a medium simmer.
Stir sauce occasionally and let cook for 35 to 40 minutes.
Taste for salt and adjust if necessary. Add squid and cook
an additional 20 minutes.
Serve over thin spaghetti or linguine.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: 5,000 calorie cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to recipe on box.
Bake in an oblong pan.
When cake is done and still hot, pour sweetened condensed milk on top.
Then add caramel.
Finally, spread on Cool Whip and chill for one hour.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In large kettle, combine jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries and juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn 1/2 mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Gently spread smooth layer of sour cream over jello.
Chill again until firm.
Then gently spoon over rest of jello and fruit mixture. Chill until firm.

title: spring fresh rice salad (sunshine salad)
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Chill.
Combine rice, celery, ham, oranges, green pepper, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with carrot curls and parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave mac-and-cheese
directions: Combine the prepared macaroni and onion.
In a 3-quart microwavable casserole, layer macaroni and onion mixture, slices of the cheese, 1/4-inch slices of margarine, salt and pepper. Cover top layer with cheese.
Pour milk over layers until casserole is 1/3 to 1/2 full.
Microwave on High power 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes to allow cheese mixture to thicken.

title: corn pudding(can be made low-fat, see options)
directions: Scald milk in 1-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat, stir in meal, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in corn. Gradually add eggs and stir vigorously.
Add other ingredients. Put in 2 1/2-quart greased baking dish and bake at 330° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together potatoes, eggs, salt, granulated sugar, 1/2 stick margarine, milk and vanilla.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix brown sugar, flour, pecans and 1/3 stick margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle this topping over the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kids snack mix
directions: Preheat oven temperature to 300°.
Place popcorn and peanuts in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan (or dish).
In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, margarine, honey and cinnamon. Cook and stir over low heat until boiling.
Boil gently, uncovered, without stirring, for 4 minutes.
Pour over popcorn mixture and stir to coat.
Bake coated popcorn in 300° oven 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Transfer to a large bowl; add Teddy Grahams.
Cool completely.
Add fruit snacks.
Store in a covered container.

title: apricot-buttermilk muffins
directions: In bowl, pour buttermilk over Bran Buds cereal.
In another bowl, combine flour and baking soda.
Stir in apricots; add brown sugar, oil and egg to cereal mixture.
Stir into flour mixture. Spoon into muffin cups.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream oleo with sugar, add eggs and bananas.
Combine the milk and vinegar.
Add dry ingredients to banana mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased baking loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In skillet over medium-high heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken until browned on both sides.
Add soup and water, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 20 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink. Serve over hot cooked rice or with rice pilaf.
Serves 4.

title: almost raspberry jam
directions: Combine tomatoes and sugar.
Simmer for 25 minutes; stir occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved, about 1 minute.
Pour into jars or plastic containers; cool.
Stir occasionally to prevent fruit from floating.
Top with lids. Refrigerate.
Yield:
7 cups.

title: beef and cheese ball
directions: With cream cheese at room temperature, add Worcestershire sauce, Accent, chopped onion and 1 package beef (chopped).
Line bowl with remaining beef.
Spoon mixture into bowl and refrigerate.
Invert onto serving dish.

title: steak and onions
directions: Cut round steak into bite size pieces. Combine round steak, soup, water and onion in microwave-safe dish and refrigerate overnight.
Microwave for 40 to 50 minutes. Can be served with rice.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a large punch bowl, crumble one layer of the baked cake. Add half the pudding, half the pineapple, 2 of the bananas, half the cherry pie filling and half the blueberry pie filling.
Put half of the Cool Whip on top, then sprinkle with half of the coconut.
Take the other cake layer and crumble on top.
Repeat as directed.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: bacon dip
directions: Place cottage cheese and milk in blender.
Blend on high until smooth and creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend on low speed until bacon is evenly distributed.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: ken's best chex mix ever
directions: Preheat oven at 250°.
Melt butter and add spices and sauce. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Stir well with butter mixture. Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Stir well every 15 - 20 minutes.
Can use a large aluminum disposable turkey roasting pan.
Once roasted cool on paper towel. Cool completely.
Store in zip lock bags or airtight containers/tins.

title: vegetable chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Add enough Miracle Whip to moisten salad to desired consistency. Can thin out salad dressing with a little milk.
Add sugar, salt and pepper to taste.

title: confectioners' sugar
directions: Blend sugar on highest speed of blender for two minutes. Add cornstarch to keep from packing. Store in an airtight container.

title: stew with ravioli dumplings
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix flour and 1/2 teaspoon of salt and dredge beef with seasoned flour.
Heat oil in saucepan. Add beef and brown well on all sides.
Add bouillon, spaghetti sauce and remaining salt and cover.
Cook over low heat for 50 minutes.
Add onions and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add frozen peas, cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Spoon ravioli on top and cover. Heat for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: eleanor's chicken rice
directions: Cook mushrooms lightly in 2 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour; add chicken stock.
Cook and stir constantly over low heat until thickened.
Add cream and salt.
Mix rice with pimento in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add chicken and cover with sauce.
With a fork, lift chicken and rice lightly so sauce will run down.
Brown almonds lightly in 1/4 cup butter; drain.
Sprinkle almonds over top of casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze all moisture out.
Mix together all other ingredients and add thawed spinach.
Again mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let set for 2 days until flavors are blended.

title: white icing
directions: Whip until creamy 3 to 5 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 pounds powdered sugar.
Whip until well mixed.
(Add sugar a pound at a time.)
Makes enough for 2 or 3 cakes.
This may be frozen for up to 1 year.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef; add tomato sauce, taco mix, olives and onion flakes.
Simmer 10 minutes. Crush tortilla chips.
Put half of the chips in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Add meat mixture.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and green chiles.
Pour over meat. Add cheese. Top with remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Cook limas for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Wash and trim carrots. Cook in 1 cup of boiling, salted water for 15 minutes or until tender. Drain.

title: texas meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in medium nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and red peppers.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in chili powder, cumin, ground red pepper and garlic.
Cook 20 seconds more. Transfer to large bowl and cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix boiling water, salt, sugar and cornstarch together; boil until clear and thick, stirring constantly.
While hot, add the jello and stir until dissolved.
Let cool completely.
Arrange sliced strawberries in pie shell and pour over cooled mixture. Refrigerate and serve with Cool Whip.

title: pizza omelet
directions: Combine all ingredients in a buttered shallow baking dish. Bake 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the omelet comes out clean.
If you're an egg lover or pizza nut, this novelty should suffice.

title: lime light pie
directions: Whip the evaporated milk.
Add sugar.
In another bowl, dissolve jello with one cup of hot water.
Add lemon juice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Line pan with vanilla wafers.
Combine jello with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pan and garnish with finely crushed wafers.

title: tex-mex chicken tenders
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, chili powder, cumin and red pepper; set aside.

title: chewies
directions: Mix this together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage brunch meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl combine eggs and milk.
Stir in bread crumbs, chopped onion, parsley, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Add sausage and ground beef. Mix well. Shape meat mixture into one-inch meatballs.
Place in baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.

title: night-before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes ten servings.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except milk and eggs, in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low 4 hours. Turn to high 4 hours (cooking time may vary; potatoes should be well softened). Stir in evaporated milk during last hours. Add eggs (if desired) just before serving.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat pudding with milk and vanilla; set aside.

title: baked beans with bacon and red onions
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Pour beans in casserole dish and place in oven.

In skillet, cook bacon 2 to 3 minutes. Add onions and cook 3 minutes longer. Slide beans out of oven, scatter onions and bacon over beans. Sprinkle brown sugar over the onions and pepper. Bake beans with toppings 10 minutes longer. Garnish with parsley.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Combine beaten eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Into a greased rectangle casserole dish, layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Repeat layer.
Pour liquid mixture over ingredients in casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot dog soup
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Drain and add rest of ingredients. Cook pasta and all ingredients until thoroughly heated and mixture has thickened a bit.
Takes about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat sugar, vinegar and salt. Bring to a boil and cool until lukewarm.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate.
Ready in 24 hours.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Shape in 1 1/2-inch balls and brown on all sides in the hot margarine.
Put in 3-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients, including salt. Arrange on top of meatballs.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fish a la russe
directions: Place onions in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Rinse fish and pat dry.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Roll up, starting at narrow end.
Place fish rolls, seam side down, on onion.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°, covered.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Slice bananas and dip in lemon juice.
In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding, mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer in a bowl:
vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Layer twice.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except biscuits and cheese.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with cheese; put biscuits on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: colonial carrot-pecan cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large size mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Add half of the flour mixture; blend.
Add remaining flour alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and pecans; mix well.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan upright. Remove from pan.

title: cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in other ingredients.

title: chicken and pasta with orange-basil sauce
directions: In large saucepan, cook pasta in slightly salted boiling water for 5 minutes. Add frozen vegetables. Return to boiling. Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes or more until pasta and vegetables are tender. Drain. Return to saucepan.

title: baked chicken breasts(low-fat)
directions: Dip chicken in skim milk.
Shake in plastic bag with corn flake crumbs until coated.
Place in baking dish sprayed with Pam. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until tender.
Cover dish with lid or foil and cook for 15 to 20 minutes for more tender and moist chicken.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Combine chocolate mix, nondairy creamer, coffee, cinnamon and powdered sugar.
Mix until well blended; store in airtight container.
Use 2 or 3 tablespoons per mug with boiling water. You may add 1 or 2 teaspoons coffee flavored liqueur if desired.

title: vanilla-butternut frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put on cake.

title: butterfly cupcakes
directions: Make pudding according to package directions, using skim milk. Let sit for 5 minutes.
Cut a cone shape from the top of each cupcake and set aside.
Fil the cavity of each cupcake with 1 tablespoon of pudding.
Cut cones in half and place two halves, flat side down, on each cupcake to represent butterfly wings. Place 1/2 teaspoon of jam in the center to resemble the body. Dust with powdered sugar.
Chocolate fans can substitute chocolate cupcakes and fill with whipped topping.

title: beets and onions
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: chalupa
directions: Cook (boil) chicken until done.
Cool and dice.
Quarter tortillas.
Mix together soups and sour cream in large bowl with milk, onion and chilies.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers and mix with butter. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and milk. Slice strawberries and mix with glaze. Put on crust. Put Cool Whip mixture on next. Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: chicken gumbo meat loaf
directions: Mix beef and undiluted soup together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: egg-in-toast
directions: Butter a slice of bread on both sides.
With the top of a large glass, press onto bread and cut out circle from center. Place in hot, buttered frying pan.
Pour 1 stirred-up egg into hole.
Fry on both sides.
Also, fry round bread piece.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until light and fluffy after each addition.
Add mashed bananas; add lemon juice.
Beat into creamed mixture. Combine dry ingredients.
Mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for approximately 1 1/4 hours.

title: ice cream party ball
directions: Line 2 (one-quart) bowls with foil.
Soften pistachio ice cream and line each bowl with it.
Freeze at least 1 hour.
Soften chocolate ice cream and layer each bowl.
Freeze again.
Fold fruit into softened vanilla ice cream.
Fill center of each bowl with this mixture.
Smooth across top and freeze hard.
Take ice cream from bowls and press together.
Cover this ball with cream that has been whipped with the sugar.
Freeze hard, wrapped in plastic.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.
May decorate with sprinkles, sauces, etc.

title: potatoes for a crowd
directions: Coat large Pyrex dish with oil.
Add frozen hash brown potatoes, thawed.
Combine in bowl and spread on potatoes 1 stick melted butter, onion, Cheddar cheese, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix and spread over potato mixture 1/2 stick butter and crushed corn flakes.
Sprinkle extra grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well. Then add milk. Add egg yolks beaten. Cook on medium heat until filling starts to thicken. Add vanilla and butter. Pour in cooked pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 1/3 cup sugar. Beat 3 more minutes. Put on pie and brown in oven until light brown.

title: snapper with cumin-citrus sauce
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, bring 2 inches of water to a simmer with bay leaf and lemon slices.
Add the fillets; cover and simmer for 4 to 6 minutes, or until fish is flakey.

title: mock peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix well and pour into buttered pan.
Let cool in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: slate run squirrel stew
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown in Dutch oven.
Add onion slices and saute for a few minutes.
Add bouillon, salt, tarragon, pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add carrots and celery.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes or until tender. Serve with hot crusty cornbread to soak up broth.

title: spaghetti stuffed chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain and add margarine, cheese, parsley and egg.
Mix well. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Start by stuffing the chicken breast under the skin. Do not tear the skin.
Push spaghetti in carefully.
You'll end up with a very fat looking chicken.
Stuff inside, tie together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place white sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Take a few pieces of biscuit and place in bag; shake, coating biscuit pieces.
Place coated biscuit pieces into a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans between layers of biscuits.

title: strawberry rum punch
directions: In blender puree 1 can lemonade and 1 package strawberries. Pour into nonmetal container.
Repeat.
Stir in grape juice and rum.
Freeze at least 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from freezer at least 20 minutes before serving.
Stir in 7-Up.

title: meat korma from india
directions: Mix the meat with turmeric and salt in a pan and boil the meat in a proportionate quantity of water.
There should not be any excess water in the pan when the meat is tender.
Add ginger, onion and yogurt to the boiled meat and keep for 20 minutes with occasional stirring.
Then fry in a little butter until brown. Ready for serving.

title: stuffed hot dogs
directions: Slice wieners; stuff with cheese.
Place in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve in warmed hot dog buns.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: In saucepan, bring mixed vegetables to a boil and cook until tender.
Saute onions in small amount of margarine or oil until just tender.
Drain vegetables and mix all other ingredients with vegetables.
Put in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dallas taco dip
directions: Combine soup and taco sauce and heat well.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Layer on onion and olives.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla and/or nacho chips.

title: lizard tails
directions: Slice cucumbers lengthwise.
Pack in clean jars 1/2 teaspoon per pint, 1 teaspoon per quart jar.
Combine remaining ingredients; heat to boil.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Pack cucumbers in jars with dill.
Pour mix ingredients over cukes.
Put in cold water; add water to cover jars.
Just bring to boil.
Remove jars immediately.
They will seal.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Beat egg in measuring cup and add cold water to measure 1/2 cup liquid.
Blend flour and shortening together.
Add liquid to flour mixture.
May be made ahead of time and wrapped in wax paper and stored in refrigerator until needed.

title: nutty cheese
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cook in a double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cream cheese, pimento and nuts.
Serve on bread as a sandwich or on crackers.

title: manhattan beef roll
directions: Blend biscuit mix and buttermilk with mixer on low speed.
Do not overmix.
Roll on floured surface into a rectangular shape approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Spread evenly over dough mixture.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice into 1-inch pieces.
Place onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve with gravy. Makes 7 servings.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine flour, oil, 2 tablespoons sugar and milk.
Mix with electric mixer.
Press into pie pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix for four minutes. Grease the pan well with shortening and flour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mustard dill sauce
directions: Put the
egg
in bowl of a food processor.
Add mustard and process
for
a
few
seconds.
Scrape down sides of bowl. With the machine running, slowly add the oil in a fine, steady stream until the mixture reaches a mayonnaise-like consistency.
Add dill
and
process
until
sauce is light green with green flakes. Place
in
container
and refrigerate.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
Also great on fish.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine and stir ingredients.
Pour in pan and spread 2 cups berries along with 1 cup sugar over batter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat with electric mixer until fluffy. Add marshmallows, pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Mix together. Serve chilled.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: great salad
directions: Add all together.
Then just pretend there are no calories.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Boil butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: swiss onion dip
directions: Saute onions in 1 Tbsp. butter.
Mix all and bake in pie pan for 15-20 minutes at 350 degrees (or nuke 3-4 minutes with one stir).

title: pork chops
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well.
Put chops on top (don't brown).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Mix all sauce ingredients together and chill.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Cut off top third of each apple.
Place bottoms of apples in apple baker.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon in small bowl; sprinkle over raisins.
Place tops of apples over sugar mixture.
Pour apple juice over apples; cover with wax paper; puncture.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High or until tender.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add pulp and sugar.	Mix flour, salt and soda. Alternate flour and milk.
Add butter and flavoring.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Raise to 400° and brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn.
Mix together the gelatin, sugar, syrup and a few drops of the food coloring; heat to a full boil.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Scald milk with onions in top of double boiler.
Add mushrooms and seasonings and cook for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix chicken broth, Ro-Tel, and mushroom soup.
Bring to a slow boil.
Add cheese and cook until melted.
Add chicken.
Heat through.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add cooked noodles to the meat mixture.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Grease or butter a large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan. Cover with crackers.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and stir until butter and sugar are mixed well.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for exactly 5 minutes.
Pour chocolate chips over crackers.
As they start to melt, spread them with a knife.
Top with chopped pecans or walnuts (optional).
Cut in squares.
It takes them a few hours to harden completely.

title: lentil chili
directions: Heat olive oil in a large heavy pot.

Saute onion, garlic and carrot until tender (5 minutes). Add water, tomato paste, lentils, peppers and beans. Break tomatoes on the side of the pan. Add to mixture. Stir in chili powder, cumin and pepper flakes. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium to low and cook about 45 minutes or until lentils are tender, but not mushy.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on rice.

title: doughgods
directions: Stretch dough long, about size of fist.
Drop in hot fat and deep fry until done.
Dip in sugar and eat!

title: sweet 'n sour slaw
directions: In small saucepan, mix together vinegar, oil, celery seed and 2 tablespoons sugar. Bring to a boil and stir until sugar dissolves. Cool. Mix green pepper, onion and cabbage. Pour 1 cup sugar and salt over and mix. Pour cooled dressing over vegetables. Chill for several hours.

title: ruth lyon's cranberry salad
directions: Cook berries in water until they pop.
Add sugar and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Let mixture cool, then add apples, celery and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: frozen chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Line 8 x 8-inch baking pan with foil.
Combine graham crackers and melted butter; mix thoroughly.
Press into bottom of pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add softened ice cream and blend thoroughly.
Pour into pan over graham crackers.
Place in freezer for 2 hours or until firm.
Melt unsweetened chocolate and drizzle over top of frozen mixture.
Return to freezer; ready to serve.

title: quick rolls
directions: Scald milk and let cool until lukewarm.
Soak yeast cake in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Mix all ingredients.
Sift enough flour in pan to make up as you would biscuits.
Make dough a little stiffer than biscuit dough. Set to rise in greased container.
Let rise until double itself.
Work again slightly on floured board. Roll out with rolling pin.
Cut out with small cutter; place in greased pan to rise.
Bake in oven (hot).
Makes about 20 rolls.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove and add soda and butter. Pour over corn. Mix to cover. Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stir every 15 minutes.
Cool, break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: high note nachos
directions: Place Doritos on cookie sheet.
Grate cheese over top of chips.
Place chilies on each chip.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until cheese melts.

title: barbecue sauce
