directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Excellent for chicken, lean pork chops.

title: ultimate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease sides and bottom of a spring-form pan (3-inches high).
Shape ready made crust to bottom of pan. Make holes with fork and bake until brown.
Meanwhile, beat cream cheese until soft.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat at high speed. Beat in eggs and yolks, one at a time, until smooth.
Beat in cream and flour.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Boil 5 minutes, then put into jars and seal.

title: scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in butter.
Beat egg in measuring cup and fill to 1 cup with milk.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Turn out on floured board and knead lightly.
Press by hand or roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased sheet for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned at 400°.

title: fried cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese with flour and seasonings.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to first mixture. Shape in small balls, roll in cracker dust and deep-fry in oil. Drain on brown paper.

title: sauteed spinach leaves
directions: Cut away and discard any tough spinach stems and blemished leaves.
Wash spinach thoroughly in cold water and drain well. Heat butter in a large skillet, then add spinach, salt and pepper to taste and nutmeg.
Stir as the spinach wilts.
Cook over medium-high and cook until the spinach leaves are thoroughly wilted.
Remove from heat and serve.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Melt 1 cube butter in one (9 x 13-inch) pan or two (8 x 8-inch) square pans.
Pour vanilla wafers over butter.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Combine chips in 2-quart glass bowl.
Cook in microwave on High power 2 minutes.
Stir.
Repeat process until mixture is melted.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper. Let cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Let set overnight; drain and add 2 cups red grapes or white ones.
Add pineapple and nuts. Fold in whipped cream.
Keep chilled until time to serve.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail well.
In bowl, cut pineapple in half. Drain cherries and cut in half.
Mix other ingredients and let set overnight.
Use Knudsen sour cream to get the good flavor.
Very good and easy.

title: southern chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut celery leaves from the choicest pieces of celery.
Put in mixture for good taste.
Add more sandwich spread if you want a creamier salad.

title: pina colada shake
directions: Blend in blender.
Each serving contains 60 calories.

title: apple pecan cream pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread half in pie crust. Refrigerate other half.
Then beat well the milk, half and half, pudding and Cool Whip.
Spread over pie mix in crust.
You can either freeze pie for 1 hour or refrigerate for 3 hours to chill. Before serving, place other half of mixture on top of pie.

title: clinton cookies fit for a president
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Beat together shortening, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and rolled oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop batter by well-rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are done. Cool cookies on sheets for 2 minutes before placing them on wire racks for further cooling.
Yield:
7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry dream delight
directions: Put pineapple, water and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add jello; dissolve, then let partially congeal.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into mold to congeal.

title: loaded potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Mash With milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix in onions, cheese, and bacon.
Place in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguine 8 minutes or as package directs for al dente. Drain well and mix with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least overnight.

title: canned jalapeno peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half and seed, wash and drain.
Pack in quart jar.
Add salt and alum.
Heat vinegar to boiling, pour over peppers and seal with hot lid.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together; pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: soft custard
directions: Scald milk. Combine eggs with sugar and salt. Stir into the milk. Cook over gently simmering water, stirring constantly, with a metal spoon, until custard begins to thicken. Remove from heat. Stir in the vanilla.
Turn into a bowl to cool, stirring occasionally, during the cooling period.

title: luscious linguine
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions.
Drain and transfer to large microwave-safe platter.
Toss with margarine. In small bowl, mix together yogurt, Blue cheese dressing, mustard and herbs and pour desired amount over linguine.
Add meat and toss lightly with 2 forks to mix.
Cover with plastic wrap, venting slightly, and heat in microwave.

title: gazpacho(cold, creamy soup.)
directions: Prepare the vegetables. Peel and wash.
Liquify in blender the carrot, cucumber, bell pepper, onion, bread and tomatoes.
Add drops of garlic juice, olive oil to taste and vinegar, if desired. Chill well.
Serve as a drink or a soup.
Very refreshing on a hot afternoon.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Prepare vegetables and add to broth.
Boil together until vegetables are just tender for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings, each 1 cup.

title: plumlee family peach conserve
directions: To facilitate peeling, drop the peaches in boiling water for a couple minutes, then in cold water. Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven or kettle. Let mixture stand for a couple hours. Boil gently until syrup is thick, about an hour. It will be thicker when it cools. Remove peach seeds. Pour into sterilized glasses and seal.

title: wahiawa refresher
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl.
Makes 20 servings.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Cut each cheese slice in half;
place one half on top of each cutlet.
Starting with a short end, tightly roll up cutlets, jelly-roll style.
Tie securely with string.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar; cut in shortening and stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Keep covered in refrigerator at least one hour before using.
Roll out and cut the biscuits.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Layer on a platter:
bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream/mayo/taco mixture, shredded lettuce, green onions, tomatoes, black olives and Monterey Jack or sharp cheese.

title: sursild(pickled salted herring)
directions: Clean herring.
Cut off tail and head and rinse well in cold running water.
Put fish into a mixture of milk and water, enough to cover.
Allow to stand 12 hours.
Remove and drain.
Make shallow cut in skin along backbone and peel off skin, putting towards tail end.
Fillet herring and cut fillets into 1-inch pieces.

title: calico quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a pie shell, layer chopped peppers, cheeses, and chicken.
In a saute pan, melt butter and saute onions until soft.
Whisk in flour thoroughly.
Stir in half and half and simmer until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Let cool.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs and sugar.
Melt and add butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: burgers in onion mushroom gravy
directions: Make 4 oval shaped burgers and brown in a large frying pan. Add onion after turning burgers.
When burgers are cooked to your liking, drain.
Add mushrooms to pan.
Mix gravy with 3/4 cup of water* and pour over burgers. Simmer for 20 minutes and then serve.

title: chicken mushroom casserole
directions: In large baking dish, mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream together.
Layer your cutlets on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/4 hour.
Add nonalcoholic beer and 1 can drained peas.
Continue baking 1/4 hour more.

title: alma sink's gingersnaps
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl with mixer, beat Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and molasses until blended.
Beat in 1 cup flour, salt, soda and spices until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Lightly grease the bottom of a flat-bottomed 3-inch glass.
Dip glass in a small bowl of sugar.
Use glass to flatten the cookies, dipping each time in the sugar.
Bake cookies for 15 minutes, until light brown.
Let stand for 1 minute.
Remove to wire racks.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight containers.

title: chicken paprikash with hungarian dumplings
directions: Simmer chicken, onions and paprika in kettle with 2 quarts of water. Simmer until tender. Skin and debone cooked chicken and break into pieces. Put chicken and Hungarian Dumplings back into chicken broth. Add salt and pepper to taste. Reheat. Add half and half and bring to a boil. Thicken. Enjoy!

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and pout into 12 muffin tins. Bake at 350°.
Batter should be thin and muffin tins about 1/4-inch full.

title: overnight coleslaw
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Sprinkle the 3/4 cup sugar over the vegetables.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until almost done.
Saute onion in butter and add cooked rice and soup.
Put in oven and bake until brown on top, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lornet's chicken macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until cooked; drain.
Boil sausage until cooked, then dice it.
Boil peas and chicken.
Shred chicken when cooled. Drain peas.
Mix together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place on serving dish.
Garnish with
parsley and pineapple slices.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat over to 350°.
Melt 1 stick of butter in 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Blend together, flour, sugar and milk.
Pour canned fruit filling in bottom of baking dish with the melted butter. Pour the batter over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Grind parsley, bell pepper, onion, celery and garlic in food processor.
Slice green onions with knife, and snip tops with scissors.
Rinse and drain beans.
Place in kettle with chopped vegetables and ham.
Pour in enough water to cover everything in pot.
Cook on very low heat for 3 hours.
Add seasonings halfway through cooking time.
Liquid will thicken to a creamy, gravy-like consistency.
Slice sausage into 1/2-inch pieces and add to beans.
Cook about 20 minutes longer.
Serve over rice. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: crab quiche
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together and add the crabmeat, then add cheese and onions and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 if cut in small wedges.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add remaining ingredients in layers in pan, pouring Eagle Brand milk on last over all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Boil chicken with salt until tender.
In a mixing bowl, combine ginger, garlic, vinegar, black pepper, cayenne, and mustard.
Dip chicken pieces into it and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour hot water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1/2 cup flour and mix thoroughly.
Stir in softened yeast half of remaining flour and egg; beat.
Add enough flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and let rest 5 to 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and grease top.
Cover with dampened towel and refrigerate.

title: tortillas roll-ups
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread on tortillas, roll up and chill.

title: never fail chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: potato soup and potato dumplings
directions: Cut up potatoes (4), carrots, onion and celery in saucepan. Add parsley and seasoning.
Grate other 4 potatoes.
Drain of liquid.
Add egg and seasoning.
Mix.
Add enough flour to make paste.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: In a large bowl, whip the milk until peaks form.
Add lemon juice and sugar and whip until well mixed.
Line 2 pie pans (or 1 large pan) with crackers and pour in mixture.
Freeze overnight.

title: baked eggs
directions: Tear bread into pieces and place in greased 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over bread pieces. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until middle is firm.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Add sour cream, vanilla, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix batter at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour half the batter into pan (greased and floured).
Top with 1/2 of cinnamon, sugar and chips.
Pour rest of batter and top with remaining cinnamon, sugar and chips. Bake.

title: italian chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in shallow dish.
Dip each chicken breast in milk and roll in crumb mixture.
Place in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes or until done.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts; when cooled, take off bone, chopping amount desired to put in casserole.
Reserve remaining chicken for top of casserole.
Cook rice as directed on package, adding the chopped onion.
Let simmer.
Heat soup as directed on can.
When rice and soup are ready, mix together, adding chopped chicken, salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Place pats of margarine on top and rest of chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix well.
Will make 30 to 36 cupcakes 1/2 full.

title: breaded broccoli
directions: Boil broccoli until crisp.
Heat garlic and oil in frying pan. Drain broccoli.
Mix bread crumbs and salt in plastic bag.
Dip broccoli in egg and milk batter.
Put broccoli in bag and shake until well covered.
Fry in already heated garlic and oil until browned.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and peanut butter.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape into walnut size balls; roll in sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar, then add one egg at a time.
Sift flour; add to the creamed mixture, small portions at a time.
Mix well.

title: quaker oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and drippings.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add beaten egg, raisins, then soda dissolved in raisin juice.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Add more flour if mixture is not thick enough.
Drop on greased cookie sheets by the teaspoon.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen large cookies.

title: mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on the bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Put the olives over the chili and then the grated Cheddar on the top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until the cheese is well melted.
Serve with taco chips.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: In a large Pyrex bowl, place the stick of butter.
Melt in oven.
While butter melts, mix together sugar, milk and flour. Remove bowl from oven; pour flour mixture into butter.
Do not mix.
Pour fruit mixture into bowl.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put spices in a cheesecloth bag and boil gently in the water and vinegar for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove bag of spices and let liquid cool.
Hard-boil eggs; cool and peel.
Pack eggs into clear canning jar; pour cool solution over and seal.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 2 days before using.
Use within 2 weeks. Sliced onion added to jar gives additional flavor.

title: picnic cake
directions: Arrange peach slices and juice evenly on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly on top of peaches.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over cake mix and top with chopped nuts.
Drizzle melted butter evenly over top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: ypders heavenly hash popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Spread popcorn in buttered jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and peanuts.
Arrange chocolate bars over top.
Place in oven.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly; toss.

title: sauerbraten stew
directions: Brown stew beef with oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer until meat is tender.
Thicken gravy with flour and water. Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Lower heat and cook until small amount forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat and add vanilla; beat until thick. Add nuts, if desired. Pour into buttered dish and let stand until set. Cut into squares and serve.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand for a while before serving. Add 1 teaspoon dill weed.

title: pizzelle(italian)
directions: You will need a pizzelle maker.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, parsley, sugar, salt and basil.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles in boiling water until done.
Mix tomato sauce and sour cream together.
In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer noodles, sauce, American cheese and Parmesan cheese (about 4 layers).
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pinto, white or navy beans
directions: Put beans in heavy pot with water and bring to boil; drain. Add fresh water to beans and bring to boil.
Add a ham hock or strip of hot jowl; also add salt and sugar.
Cook about 2 hours or until tender.
You will need to add more water during cooking time.
Reduce heat to medium-low.

title: jello salad
directions: This salad will serve 24 people.
Mix all ingredients and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix together butter, sugar and egg. Stir in yeast mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Bake in greased muffin tins for about 20 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: pineapple jelly
directions: Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly, for about 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour into canning jars, wiping tops of jars to make sure they are clean.
Put on tops and bands to seal.

title: stacked enchiladas
directions: Mix enchilada sauce and picante sauce.
Tile bottom of 9x13 greased pan with tortillas so completely covered.
Split open green chilies and layer on tortillas.
Mix meat and beans together and spread half over chilies.
Pour half the sauce over and top with 1/3 of the cheese.
Repeat layers and top with a layer of tortillas and the rest of the cheese.
Bake at 350 for 30-45 minutes or until cheese on top is melted and brown.
Let stand 15-20 minutes out of oven, then cut into squares.

title: stars and stripes dessert
directions: Slice 1 cup strawberries; set aside.
Halve remaining strawberries; set aside.
Line bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with cake slices.
Top with 1 cup sliced strawberries, 1 cup blueberries and cover top with Cool Whip.
Use strawberry halves and 1/3 cup blueberries to create a flag design.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: granny's homemade bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Then mix the remaining ingredients together. Let rise to double in size.
Make into rolls or loaf. Bake at 375°.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Peel apples and slice thin. Add white sugar and cinnamon, then mix.
Pour into a
9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour water over all. Combine butter, brown sugar and flour.
Mix together well. Add nuts.
Pour mixture over top of apples.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and Pet milk to a boil.
Boil 7 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream.
Add peanut butter and mix well. Put pan in cold water and stir until hard to stir.

title: seeber salad
directions: Prepare jello with 1 cup hot water to each box (not cold water!).
Add sweetened condensed milk (might look curdled).
Add the crushed pineapple.
Add mayonnaise to cottage cheese.
Add cottage cheese mixture to jello mixture.
Add horseradish.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate until set, then serve.

title: mandelmusser(a swedish cookie tart)
directions: Add 4 cups of flour carefully to creamed mixture.
Additional flour may be needed to work dough easily and fill your tart tin forms.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove tins from oven and turn over carefully to remove tart from tin.
Cool and store gently in airtight container.

title: spicy turkey patties or meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shape into 4 patties. Grill until done. These can also be shaped into meatballs and baked in the oven or fried in a skillet. You may also wish to try this in turkey chili.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper, onions and sugar; mix well. Mix oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
When cold, store in refrigerator or freezer.
Let stand 3 days.
Will keep for a month.
Store in an airtight container.

title: angel squares
directions: Make a dough of flour, margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks by blending with fingers in a bowl.
Pat dough mixture into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Prick dough with a fork and bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and spread with jam.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into frozen pie shell. Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: best rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good ain't it?
Now begin.
Select a large bowl, measuring cup, etc. Check the rum again, it must be just right.
To be sure rum is of the highest quality, pour 1 level cup into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cut strawberries and place in prepared crust.
Combine sugar, water and cornstarch; cook over medium heat until clear like water.
Add Jell-O; mix and pour over the top of strawberries. Makes 1 pie.

title: dip
directions: For larger groups, double or triple.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with stuffing mix, reserving a small amount for topping.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spread over stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with reserved stuffing mix.
Bake for several minutes longer or until brown.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add flour, 7-Up and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in Bundt pan.
Enjoy!

title: banana split dessert
directions: Break cake in small pieces.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan with bananas.
Pour mixed pudding over cake and bananas.
Add a layer of pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Cool and serve.

title: "special surprise" cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well until blended.
Sift cocoa, flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Add alternately to first mixture with water.
Blend well.
Add washed, drained and finely chopped sauerkraut.
Blend.

title: fat-free microwave mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Put in a 5-quart glass bowl (large electric mixer bowl works).
Pour in 1 cup milk.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes. Remove. Add 1 cup milk and mash a little (to prevent boil over).
Return to microwave for 10 to 15 more minutes.
Remove. Add salt, pepper and Butter Buds to taste. Mash or whip. Since you don't drain potatoes, they retain all their nutrients and flavor.

title: hot chicken salad recipe
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
This recipe is good for large groups.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine 2 mixtures.
Chill at least 15 minutes. Makes 4 single crusts.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Fill 6 or 8 green bell peppers, cored and seeded, with mixture.
Top with the remaining tomato sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: veggie squares
directions: *Amounts to your taste; chop enough to cover a cookie sheet size.

title: pumpkin cheese cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer, combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice; mix on low until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.

title: mulled wine punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except wine, in 3 to 3 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat in microwave, covered for 20 minutes or until warmed and temperature of 160° is reached.*
Remove spices by straining.
Stir in wine.
Serve warm or cold.
*Use the Auto Temp control system to cook to 160° if your microwave has this feature.

title: russian chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add chicken and garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion.
Cook covered over low heat (juices from chicken and onion should supply enough moisture) for 30 to 40 minutes.
Juice will brown and cook away, allowing chicken to brown on bottom.
When pieces are turned over, water may be added to ensure that chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Pour maple syrup over chicken; simmer for 2 to 5 minutes.
Water may be added to skillet at any time as needed.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Thaw Cool Whip and lemonade in refrigerator. Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crusts. Chill.

title: thrown together soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions and potatoes.
Cook potatoes and onions until done.
Add to soup mixture.

title: pumpkin ice cream
directions: Soften ice cream in bowl.
Stir it and fold in remaining ingredients, except gingersnaps.
Pour over crushed gingersnaps in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add coconut and nuts; brown lightly and set aside.
Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/4 mixture in each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 jar caramel on each pie.
Sprinkle 1/4 coconut mixture on each pie.
Repeat layers, then freeze.
Serve frozen.
Yields 2 pies.

title: kavring(norwegian cookies)
directions: Line baking pan with foil.
Put desired number of pieces on foil.
Salt the fish.
Bring foil up over the fish, covering completely.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: overnight slaw
directions: In bowl, combine the cabbage, onion, peppers and olives.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir for 1 minute.
Pour over vegetables and stir gently.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: chocolate eclair refrigerator dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix the pudding and milk as directed.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread half pudding mixture over first layer of graham crackers, then place another layer of graham crackers on top of pudding.
Spread other half of pudding over second layer of graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers over last half of pudding mixture.
Cover with chocolate icing.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots, sugar and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Place in large strainer or colander.
Add celery and raisins.
Mix and let stand for 30 minutes.
Stir in mayo and mix well.
Let stand over sink for 15 to 20 minutes so extra mayo can drain.
Serve in scoops on bed of lettuce.
Refrigerate to store.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: connie's easy chocolate cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Beat three minutes on medium speed while scraping bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (greased) and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potluck potato salad
directions: I add white pepper to taste and 1 tablespoon mustard.

title: curried vegetables
directions: In large skillet on medium heat, saute onion.
Stir in curry powder, tomatoes and paste.
Add 1 cup water.
Bring to boil.
Add cut vegetables.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add stripped bell pepper, green beans and chickpeas.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Stir in yogurt. Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marinade for grilling
directions: Mix together.
Marinate for 24 to 48 hours.
Good for chicken or beef.
Great for beef, green peppers and onions on a skewer or kabobs.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly in large bowl.
Roll into large balls (about 10 to 12).
Fry in hot oil for about 3/4 hour.
Add a clove or 2 of garlic in oil.
Use any sauce (canned, jar or homemade).

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, salt and milk.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture dropped from spoon into cold water forms a firm ball.
Remove from heat. Stir in margarine, vanilla, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Mix real well.
Pour into greased pan.
Let set.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: old-fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Heat milk and melt butter in it.
Pour milk over egg mixture and mix well. Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust and bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Pie is done when puffed across top.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Pour in jar and refrigerate for 48 hours.
Cook noodles, cool and drain.
Add red onion, pimento and cucumber.
Pour in the jar mixture and chill 24 hours.

title: wash day cake
directions: For the first layer, mix cake mix, first 2 eggs and margarine. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 more eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour over the first layer.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mounds balls
directions: Let mashed potatoes cool before using.
Combine all ingredients, except paraffin and chocolate chips, well.
Shape into small balls.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Dip in combination of melted chocolate and paraffin.
Refrigerate to harden.
Store in a tight container.

title: nut moon cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla gradually, creaming well (use fingers).
Add nuts and flour little by little, so not all of it is added at one time.
Chill until firm.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl, adding 7-Up last.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice meat thin; grease skillet lightly.
Brown meat.
Push meat to one side.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in broth, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Add green peppers.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with water. Stir gradually into meat mixture.
Stir until thickens and boils. Boil 1 minute while stirring.
Add tomatoes.
Serve over rice.

title: ginger dip
directions: Sliver or mince candied ginger.
Cut cream cheese in chunks and set aside to soften.
Mix 3 ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator 2 to 3 days to mingle flavors.
Serve in ball, or flattened ball, frosted with sliced almonds if desired.
Waverly Wafers or any slightly sweet, non-salty crackers to accompany. Good with white wine.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix; spread evenly in pan.
Layer remaining as listed (avocado, sour cream, black olives, tomatoes, onion, chilies and cheese).
Makes 6 cups.

title: fred's herbed oil marinade
directions: Mix well in glass bowl.
Use oil marinade for leaner types of tilefish, rockfish, monkfish, bass, swordfish, shark steaks, cod, haddock or snapper.
Use for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beefy rice salad sandwiches
directions: Brown meat and onion. Stir in thyme.
Combine rice, red pepper and parsley in a bowl.
Add meat mixture; mix well.
Pour oil over meat mixture.
Season with salt and pepper if desired.
Fill pita shells (halves) with lettuce and tomatoes.
Add meat-rice mixture to shells.
Ready to eat.
You may also add shredded cheese (any flavor), if desired.

title: pasta with crabmeat fra diavolo
directions: In 2 or 3-quart saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic and red pepper.
Saute until onion is softened.
Add sherry and simmer 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes and seasonings, bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add crabmeat and half and half, stir well to combine.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Lightly grease baking dish.
Layer potatoes and onions.
Top with ham.
Salt to taste.
Pour soup and milk mixture over all and bake one hour or until potatoes are done in 350° oven.

title: evelyn's yeast bread
directions: Put sugar and shortening in a large mixing bowl and stir in hot water until shortening melts.
Set aside to cool.
(If water is too hot when you add the yeast, it will kill the yeast.)
When cool, add eggs and yeast mixture and blend well.
Add salt and flour and mix until blended.
Use after doubled in size.
Unused dough must be stored in the refrigerator.
Make into rolls.
Cook at 400° until brown.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: mr. bonds' tuna salad
directions: Chop or grate all ingredients fine.
Mix with tuna, Miracle Whip and picante sauce.
Use amounts according to amount you want in the amount of tuna fish you use.

title: bride's rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening. (If using oil, hot tap water will work.)
Add sugar and salt. Blend and cool. Add eggs. Dissolve yeast in warm water; add egg mixture.
Add flour to make soft dough.
You may need a little more or less than 10 cups flour.
Knead until smooth and refrigerate.
Make into rolls 1 to 2 hours before baking.
Bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes. Keeps well in refrigerator for about 10 days.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: green rice
directions: Use a 2-quart heavy saucepan with a tight fitting lid.
Heat the pan and add the oil and 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Add the onions, parsley and spinach.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Mix in the rice and stir until translucent.
Add 2 cups of the hot chicken stock, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat, about 10 minutes.
Add the remaining broth.
Cover and cook another 10 minutes or until the rice is tender.
Lightly mix in the remaining butter with a fork.
Garnish with the cheese topping.

title: potato parmesan chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Do not drain. Make a white sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add undrained vegetables.
Heat; add cheese and bacon, stirring until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.
This recipe doubles easily.

title: slovak christmas soup
directions: Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
(Add water, if necessary, while heating.)

title: stuffed tomatoes and peppers
directions: Cover bottom of frying pan with olive oil.
Add onions, garlic and pepper.
Saute and then add the ground beef, parsley, mint, salt and pepper and oregano.
Saute and then add rice and tomatoes.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Fill tomatoes and peppers and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: *Nut
meats
may be added to hot mixture before pouring if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin on bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 tablespoon flour.
Add chunks of butter and cheese (use your own judgment as to the amount).
Do another layer like the first; pour 1/2 can cream of celery soup (thinned) over second layer.
Fix 2 more layers, like first.
Add rest of cream of celery soup.
Put lots of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour (more or less).

title: apricot bread
directions: Sift flour and soda together; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients except for the eggs and cook in saucepan for 5 minutes; cool.
Add eggs and flour mixture to cooled fruit mixture.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Cook meat and drain off fat.
Spoon sausage into a large bowl. Cool completely.
Add cheese, biscuit mix and water.
Mix with fork just until blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on large cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and browned.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut apples into thin slices and put in bottom of prepared 9 x 13-inch pan in layers.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Beat 2 eggs and stir into mixture.
Spoon mixture over sliced apples.
Melt 1/4 stick margarine and pour over mixture, then sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix together butter and cocoa.
Add eggs and sugar to butter and cocoa mixture.
Blend flour, pecans, vanilla and salt into the above.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in a greased 9 x 13 oblong pan. Cover with miniature marshmallows.
Brown in oven.
Cool cake. Combine powdered sugar and cocoa, add milk and melted butter.
Beat well and spread on cake.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat.
Cut meat into 1-inch strips.
Brown on low heat. Pour off excess fat.
Add onion and bell pepper (cut in strips). Add water and beef broth.
Simmer with top on for 5 minutes.
Add flour and stir on low for 20 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Spread drained pinto beans over the cornbread. Chop bell pepper, onion and tomato and spread over the pintos. Make a dressing of the mayonnaise and pickle juice. Drizzle over salad and finish off with bacon.

title: sauteed chicken and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni halfway; drain.
Set aside.
Saute chopped onion.
Add garlic and chicken pieces until it turns white.
In separate bowl, mix tomato paste, pepper, turmeric, chicken soup mix, cayenne and salt.
Add this mixture to skillet with chicken and mix well to cover.

title: orange slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 5 quarts.
Freeze.
Great to serve at breakfast or anytime and nice to make ahead for company.

title: library punch
directions: Pour cold Cherry 7 Up in the punch bowl. Scoop Sherbet on top. It foams and cools.

title: steak ala edwardo
directions: In a large frying pan, saute the Italian herb seasoning, onion and garlic in oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Flatten the steaks and serrate both sides with a sharp knife.
Add the steaks to the pan and brown over high heat for a few minutes on each side.
Mix the mustard with the red wine in a small bowl.
Pour the mixture over the steaks and cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes (depending on your preference).
Use a knife and fork to check the center of the steaks for pinkness.
Serve immediately with the sauce poured over the steak.

title: mamma grisanti's house salad
directions: Mix together ingredients, then add dressing.
Mix again.

title: clams on toast
directions: Drain and reserve 1/3 cup of the liquid from the clams.
Chop the clams more finely.
Heat the oil in a skillet and saute the onion slowly until soft.
Add the garlic, parsley and pepper. Cook for a couple of minutes, then stir in the flour.
Add the reserved clam juice and the clams and heat until the mixture is thick enough to spread.
Spread on toast and reheat quickly in a 400° oven when ready to serve.

title: curried macadamia rice(servings:  4)
directions: Melt butter in skillet; cook raw rice and onion in pan for a few minutes, stirring well.
Add curry, broth and raisins.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 15 minutes and add nuts.
Stir well; cover and simmer another 5 minutes.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Blend together until smooth.
Spread on English muffin halves. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Cut into bite-sized pieces and serve.

title: potato-mushroom soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and cook until done.
Do not drain unless there is excessive water. Add mushroom soup and extra mushrooms, if desired.
Thoroughly heat through.
You may add a small amount of milk if this is too thick.
Garnish with parsley when served.

title: easy mexican layer dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Cover with chili.
Add the cheese.
Top with peppers.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: manicotti
directions: Combine eggs, parsley, Parmesan cheese, Ricotta and Mozzarella for filling.
Refrigerate until ready to stuff shells.
Cook shells and drain.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to thicken.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons Jell-O to the thickened mixture. Add the peaches. Pour into graham cracker shell. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths and put in paper bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Shake until each biscuit is covered.
Grease tube pan. Place your favorite fruit or nuts in bottom of pan.
Then put biscuits on top.
Melt butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Pour over biscuits in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, turn upside down and enjoy.

title: best dressing for salads
directions: Stir all ingredients together until well blended. Store in jar in refrigerator. Shake each time before using. Keeps well.

title: steak and pepper melt
directions: In large skillet, saute pepper and onion rings in margarine until crisp-tender; remove from skillet.
In same skillet, cook each sandwich steak as directed on package.
Fold each steak in half crosswise.
Top each folded steak with cheese slice.
Cover skillet; cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Place each steak on bottom half of roll; top with pepper and onion rings. Replace top half of roll.
Makes 2 sandwiches.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with parchment paper. In large bowl, stir together the flour, salt, baking soda and oats; set aside.
Melt margarine.
Add sugars, banana and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Add margarine to flour ingredients until forms dough.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: crawfish au gratin
directions: Combine margarine and onions over low heat, saute for 5 minutes. Add crawfish, salt and pepper; simmer 10 minutes. In double boiler, combine cheese, milk and egg yolks. Mix cornstarch with water. Add to cheese mixture and let boil for 5 minutes. Pour crawfish mixture into cheese mixture and blend well. Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Combine sugar, water and spices in a 4-cup glass measuring cup.
Microwave at High 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature at least 1 hour.
When ready to serve, strain the sugar-spice mixture into a 3-quart casserole or large mixing bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes, or until hot.
Pour into cups or mugs and serve immediately. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: liz's play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook over medium heat until mix pulls away from sides of pan and becomes like the store bought kind.
Knead until cool.
For sparkle dough, add glitter in the beginning.
Keep this separate from other colors.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in plastic container in refrigerator.
Lasts months.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°, glass pan to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 25-30 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple shrimp
directions: Pour juice from pineapple into a small bowl.
Add 1/2 teaspoon oil, soy sauce, garlic, ginger and red pepper; mix well.
Add shrimp.
Toss well and cover, refrigerate one hour.
Drain shrimp, reserve marinade.

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and honey. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.

title: jill's apple puffs
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add sugar, walnuts, pumpkin pie spice and apples that have been peeled, cored and chopped.
Mix to a rather stiff batter with eggs and milk. Drop by spoonful into hot oil and cook until puffs are golden brown and apples are tender.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; add water and cocoa and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring slightly.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet (with rim).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: split pea soup with kielbasa
directions: Wash peas well and add to water with the ham bone, onion and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bone and puree the peas through a strainer or in a blender; return to pan and add remaining ingredients, reserving some of the kielbasa for garnish when ready to serve.
Cook slowly for another hour.
Salt to taste.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Combine eggs, vinegar and sugar in top of a double boiler. Cook until thick and creamy.
Add butter and mix well.
While mixture is still hot, pour over marshmallows, fruit cocktail and bananas.
Fold in whipping cream.
Let stand in the refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: jumbo cereal muffins
directions: Mix flours with baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, milk, egg and oil.
Add to flour mixture and mix just until all flour is moistened.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Pour into 6 paper baking cup-lined 6-ounce custard cups.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 jumbo muffins or 12 medium muffins.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl. Beat good.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to shortening mixture.
Mix good.
Stir in oats.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and spread in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 23 minutes.
Spread immediately with chocolate chips; sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into bars immediately.
Cool and serve.

title: quick meatless lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, 1/2 of the Mozzarella and 1/4 cup Parmesan together.
Layer 1/4 of sauce, 3 noodles, 1/3 Ricotta in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Repeat layers twice, ending with sauce.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: spinach triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thaw and drain spinach.
Spray a nonstick skillet with nonstick olive oil spray.
Saute onion and garlic, add spinach and blend well.
In a large bowl, combine cheeses and oregano with spinach mixture.
Spray 1 sheet of phyllo with nonstick spray.
Place another sheet on top.
Spray and repeat with a third sheet.
Make four sets of three sheets each and cut each stack lengthwise into six strips (a total of 24). Cover strips with damp cloth to prevent drying.

title: best ever barbecue
directions: Cook in crock-pot until well done.
Let cool and string meat. Pour off liquid from roast and place meat back in crock-pot.
Then pour barbecue sauce over meat and let simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Combine juice of cherries and pineapple; heat.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add Cokes and fruit.
Chill.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper while still warm. Refrigerate until cool.

title: green onion teasers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well. Cut each slice of bread into 4 triangles and toast on both sides.
Spread about 1 teaspoon green onion mixture on each triangle.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix first seven ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise and mustard. Toss with mixture.
Chill several hours.
Add chow mein noodles just before serving.
Turn into lettuce lined bowl.

title: pepperoni bread rolls
directions: Let bread dough partially thaw and raise.
Cut each loaf into eight pieces.
Roll dough to approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Place two or three slices of pepperoni and a piece of cheese, if desired, on dough.
Roll up dough, tucking ends under.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blue ribbon pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat well after each egg.
Add flavoring, flour, baking powder, milk and mix alternately.
Add nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let set for 30 minutes to cool.

title: southern sausage stew
directions: Put tomatoes and frozen greens in skillet. Stir over medium heat until thawed. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Combine soup and 1/2 can of water; bring to boil.
Put drained broccoli into baking dish.
Then cover with soup.
Next sprinkle cheese on top. Then sprinkle cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
One cup of cooked rice can be added, if desired.

title: five-cup fruit salad
directions: Toss fruit, coconut and marshmallows with sour cream.
Chill and serve.

title: sonora casserole
directions: Brown in skillet hamburger and onions.
Add mushroom soup, chicken soup, green chiles and evaporated milk.
Grate cheese. Tear tortillas into pieces.
Starting with meat mixture, layer twice in a 2-quart casserole (tortillas, meat, cheese, etc.).
End with cheese.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla and condensed milk until smooth. Add lemon juice and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill several hours.

title: scones(12 scones)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Work in shortening until crumb-like. Save 1 tablespoon egg white.
Beat remaining eggs and add milk to make soft dough.
Roll 1/2-inch thick; cut into 3-inch squares. Cut square into 2 triangles.
Place on cookie sheet; brush with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: barley casserole
directions: Fry hamburg, drain off fat.
Mix rest of ingredients together and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: english toffee candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and water.
Cook to 300°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Lay 4 Hershey bars on top.
Spread lightly when melted.
Sprinkle pecans on top; break into pieces when hard. This freezes well.

title: kathy's chocolate pie
directions: Make graham or regular pie crust; put in pie dish and bake accordingly.

title: banana nut ice cream
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour in ice cream can of freezer. Fill remaining space with milk, allowing room for ice cream expansion. Follow freezer directions.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream powdered sugar and margarine.
Add flour and salt.
Pat down smoothly in a greased and floured 9x13 inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
While this is cooking prepare filling as directed.
Once done with filling, spread filling over cooked crust, reduce temperature to 325 degrees and bake for 25 minutes. Let cool completely in pan.
Cut into squares and dust with powdered sugar.

title: debbie's creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Melt butter and saute onion and garlic.
Cook potatoes and celery in broth until tender.
Add cauliflower pieces and cook 7 to 10 minutes more.
Puree this mixture and return to pan.
Add coriander, nutmeg, white pepper and salt.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in light half and half cream.
Reheat, but do not boil.

title: guess again...carrots!
directions: Pare, slice and cook carrots until tender.
Drain; mash well. Add butter, onion and cheese.
Put into a buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until browned a bit. Garnish with parsley or sprinkle top with buttered crumbs.
Serves 8.

title: cream filling for pie
directions: Mix flour and water together. Add egg yolks and sugar to the flour mixture. Stir in milk slowly. Cook in double boiler over medium heat. Cook until thickened. Pour into a prebaked pie crust.

title: angel cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and vanilla.
Using mixer, mix until just blended.
This will be a stiff dough.
Add pecans.
Put 1/3 of dough onto waxed paper and roll into a 1 1/2-inch cylinder.
Refrigerate 30 minutes before slicing (may be frozen).
Cut in 3/8-inch slices and place 1/2-inch apart on a cookie sheet that has been lined with a brown paper sack.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Combine and shake all ingredients, except peel.
Pour into tall glass.
Garnish rim with curled strip of orange peel (or slice or orange).
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix with fork the oleo (butter), cake mix and one egg.
Dough should be very dry.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Mix in small bowl the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar (reserve 2 tablespoons powdered sugar for topping).
Spread mix on top of dough and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cake puffs but settles in the center when cooled.
Sprinkle rest of sugar on top.

title: ham and broccoli bake(this is a complete dinner.)
directions: *May be cooked ahead of time to cut down on cooking time.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper; let set.

title: cinnamon and nut pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for one crust pie as directed, except roll into rectangle 14 x 8-inch.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread with margarine.
Mix nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle lengthwise over half of the rectangle.
Moisten edges with water.
Fold rectangle lengthwise in half.
Press edges together to seal.
Flute.
Prick top of pastry in several places with fork.
Brush with egg white.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Cut into slices.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix cream cheese in bowl adding confectioners sugar (small amount) to taste.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions. Cut crust off angel food cake and dice into small cubes.
Fold Dream Whip and cream cheese together.
Fold cake cubes into mixture.
Spread out in pan and top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Beat with mixer until thoroughly blended.
Add remaining ingredients, blend.
Form into ball and roll in ground nuts.
Chill until firm.
Serve with favorite snack crackers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Puree strawberries.
Put Cool Whip in large bowl.
Add strawberries.
Mix well.
Add Jell-O and pudding.
Fold in, then stir well.
Put into two 9-inch graham cracker pie shells.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla, then stir in dry ingredients. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put salt over cucumbers, onions and peppers and let stand 1 hour.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and pour over mixture.
May be refrigerated in jars or 1 large container.

title: mary's lemon squares
directions: Mix well with whisk.
Pour filling into crust as it comes out of oven.
Then return to oven and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mom's fudge pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine with cocoa in heavy saucepan over medium heat. Remove from heat and add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.*
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Do not overbake; should be slightly gooey inside.)
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: brajole(stuffed flank steak)
directions: Roll up each piece snugly and tie with string or secure with toothpicks.
Brown in olive oil.
Then put into Spaghetti Sauce* and simmer 1 to 3 hours.
Serve over spaghetti or other pasta.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight jar.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into two pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Combine zucchini and onion in 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Add cheese, pimento, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Beat eggs and hot pepper sauce together. Pour over mixture.
Microwave on Medium power 8 to 10 minutes, until center is set.
Stir halfway through cooking.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries in 2 cups sugar and let set overnight.
Mix jello; add all other ingredients, then add to cranberries.
Chill 1 or 2 days.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Put cold milk in a deep narrow bowl.
Pour Dream Whip powder over milk.
Use whatever flavor you want or need for the pudding mix (chocolate, lemon, vanilla, pistachio, etc.). Pour pudding mix in bowl.
Beat slowly until blended, then beat on high speed until frosting forms peaks, 4 to 6 minutes.
Spread on cake. Refrigerate for 2 hours before cutting.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks lightly.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk in microwave safe bowl;
mix well. Microwave on Medium-High for 7 minutes or until thickened, stirring twice.
Stir a small
amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolk; stir egg yolks into hot mixture.
Microwave on Medium-High until custard coats metal spoon, stirring once.
Beat in butter and vanilla until butter is melted.
Layer vanilla wafers, banana slices and custard alternately in bowl.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel cooked potato.
Mash with salt and butter.
Add sugar, 1/3 at a time, beating until smooth and well blended.
Mix in vanilla.
If mix is not stiff enough to roll, add more sugar. Roll out between 2 sheets of wax paper until 1/8-inch thick; spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill for one hour, then slice into 1/4-inch pieces.
Let ripen a day before eating.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and rest of ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake until done (20 to 25 minutes).

title: pork and beans
directions: Heat onion and syrup in pan over low heat until onion is cooked.
Add beans.
Heat until hot.
Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with bread crumbs.
Put 1/2 crumbs in bottom of greased pan.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl.
Pour over crumbs.
Put the remainder on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Press all liquid from sauerkraut and mix with sour cream. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Spread mixture on bread slice.
Add corned beef and cheese.
Spread hot mustard or horseradish on other slice of bread and top sandwich.
Wrap sandwiches individually in foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Put the margarine and oil in skillet and brown meat.
Put the tomato sauce and 1/2 can water in pan to keep meatballs warm until time to serve.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir
until
sugar
and
egg are well mixed into peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a
fork
dipped
in sugar, if desired.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: perfect pesto
directions: Place in blender or food processor and puree until smooth. Use immediately
or freeze in small containers for later use.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preset oven to off.
Place children and/or husband in car. Drive to nearest restaurant.
Let each member of family order their favorite dinner.
Return home and relax.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops, dip in beaten eggs and then in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot fat until browned.
Place on rack in covered roaster and put a tablespoon of catsup on each.
Make thin gravy from fat they were fried in and pour in bottom of roaster, a little water may need to be added later.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in preheated oven at 300°.

title: barbecue pork chops(greek style)
directions: Wash pork chops, if desired, with cool water.
Place in meat marinator or shallow casserole dish.
Mix juice, oil and spices and pour over chops.
Marinate for 1 to 2 hours.
Grill chips over charcoal about 20 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Saute celery and onion in 1 stick margarine.
Add mixture to bread, mixing well.
Add chicken broth to make bread stick together.
Add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste.
Mix in apples and add more broth, until all is very soft and juicy. Place in heavy baking pan and bake in 450° oven until brown. Chicken or turkey broth may be used.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop on cookie sheet to set.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Combine fruit and all juice.
Fill lined cupcake tins. Freeze.
Makes about 42.

title: crab stuffed cod
directions: Saute over medium heat the onion, garlic, green pepper, mushrooms and butter.
Add crabmeat, cracker crumbs and cheese. Cut fish in half and stuff with crab mixture.
Fold back together. Place in buttered pan and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Stir together shortening and water until smooth and creamy. Add dry ingredients all at once to shortening and water.
Mix into ball.
Divide into 3 parts.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: cherry - chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix all of above.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs.
Mash banana and add to the oleo with the eggs and salad dressing.
Mix in flour, salt and soda.
Add the water and the nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked stuffed salmon
directions: Rub inside with lemon juice and salt.
Saute celery, celery leaves and onions in butter.
Put bread in bowl; add vegetables. Add beaten eggs, herbs and salt and pepper.
Stuff fish and sew shut.
Bake at 375° to 400° for approximately 10 minutes per inch at thickest part.
Serve with a sauce made of equal parts of butter and lemon juice.

title: old-fashioned hot cocoa
directions: Bring water to a boil in small heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cocoa powder, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Place over very low heat and simmer very gently just until the mixture has reached a slightly syrupy consistency, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: You will need one large Reynolds oven bag.

title: raisin fudge squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Add raisins. Mix and add dry ingredients. Bake in greased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend Oreos and set aside.
Blend margarine and cream cheese and set aside.
Fold Cool Whip into chocolate pudding and milk. Alternate layers of cookie crumbs with pudding mixture and margarine cream cheese mixture. Start and end with cookie crumbs.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a buttered 9 x 13 baking dish, place the drained pineapple chunks.

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook beef and onions until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.
Put 1/3 of meat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 of potatoes on top.
Repeat layering, ending with meat mixture.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove foil. Sprinkle with cheese.
Let set 10 minutes for easier cutting.

title: marinated vidalias
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Combine water, sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves.
Pour over rings.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Drain well.
Stir in mayonnaise and celery seed.
Serve on lettuce leaves (or omit celery seed and lettuce and serve as a salad).

title: homemade bailey's irish cream
directions: Whip in blender to combine all ingredients. Store in airtight jar in refrigerator (lasts 2 weeks). Shake before each use.

title: nut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour one 10-inch tube pan. Blend all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.

title: good banana pudding filling
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together.
Add milk and egg yolks and cook.
Add margarine, vanilla and marshmallows and beat until marshmallows are dissolved.
Add this to Cool Whip.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until cake tester comes clean.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: cinnamon fruit dip
directions: Blend sour cream with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours to blend flavors.
Stir before serving with fresh fruit.

title: easy chicken dish
directions: Roll out crescent rolls.
Put 1/2 of the cut-up chicken on the rolled out dough.
Roll it up and place in a baking dish.

title: cream cheese egg biscuits
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Roll into balls, using flour if necessary to prevent sticking.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil
leaves.
Combine rest of ingredients except tomato paste and
water.
Roll mixture in cabbage leaves and place in crock-pot.
Pour
tomato
paste
and water mixture over cabbage rolls.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix in shortening.
Add milk and mix well.
(The dough should be easy to handle and hold together.)
Turn out onto a floured surface.
Flour your hands and gently knead the dough to form a smooth ball.
Flatten with your hands and roll dough out to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a biscuit cutter and place biscuit on greased cookie sheet.
Roll leftover dough back into a ball, roll out and cut again.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rice krispies coconut balls
directions: Melt butter, add sugar and dates; stir well.
Add beaten eggs and cook until soft ball stage, stirring constantly, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts, pour over the Rice Krispies. Mix well.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: company hamburger casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Brown hamburger and onion together; drain off fat.
Add beef to rice, then add soy sauce, mushrooms and soup.
Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: joan's bean soup
directions: Let beans soak in water for about an hour until they start to swell. Pour off the water, add ham bone or ham hocks.
Add enough water to cover the ham bone and beans.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for about 4 or 5 hours.

title: chicken on dried beef circle
directions: Place dried beef circle on bottom of baking dish (ungreased). Place one chicken breast on each mound and cover with sour cream and mushroom soup that has been mixed together.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
I use 2 circles of dried beef and this recipe seems to appeal to hearty appetites.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, milk, butter and salt; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Stir until smooth and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding with milk according to package directions. Fold in whipped topping.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with layer of cracker squares; cover with half of pudding mixture, then crackers.
Spread remaining pudding on top and cover with more crackers.
Frost with fudge frosting.
Chill.
Cut in squares.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In mixer bowl, beat shortening and butter for 30 seconds.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in oats.
Place by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry nut bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix flour, oats, sugar, pecans, soda & butter.
Mix at low speed until crumbly.
Save 1 1/2 c. of mix for topping.
Press the rest of the mix in a 13x9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 min.
Spoon pie filling evenly over crust. Sprinkle marshmallows and remaining crumbs over top.
Return to oven for 25-35 minutes.

title: maple syrup
directions: Heat sugars, water and cream of tartar in medium saucepan to boiling.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add maple flavoring.
Store in cool place in tightly closed bottle or jar.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix together flour, corn meal, salt and pepper.
In separate bowl, mix together vinegar and buttermilk.
Dip tomatoes in buttermilk mixture and roll in dry mixture on both sides.
Fry in hot oil 2-inches deep.
Turn once with tongs.
(Do not use fork.) Drain in colander.
(Do not use paper towels.
Will make tomatoes soggy.)
Do not stack tomatoes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Wash raisins and drain.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat egg.
Add milk and add to sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal and raisins; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: french-style pizza
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Slice rolls lengthwise.
Spread with prepared
pizza
sauce, ground beef,
pepperoni
slices, olives, mushrooms and top with grated cheese.
Bake
8 minutes in a 300° oven.
Serves 6.

title: creamy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
In a bowl mix crumbled egg yolks and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refill yolks.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put 2 cans of beans in casserole dish. Spoon over 1/2
soup, mushrooms, sour cream, salt and soup mix. Then the rest of the beans and remaining ingredients. Spread a layer of buttered crumbs, dry bread or cracker, over top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: texas-sized almond crunch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, blend 1 cup sugar, powdered sugar, margarine and oil until well mixed.
Add almond extract and eggs; mix well.

title: harding pie(mrs. harding served this to her guests and family.)
directions: Mix together and put into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown and center is set.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Melt chocolate and pour over all ingredients which have been mixed together.
Mix until everything has been coated with chocolate.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: spring salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Place in bowl.
Add onion and bacon bits.
Combine sour cream, mayo and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Pour over vegetables; stir and chill for 20 minutes before serving.

title: aunt dot's hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
The corn is the only liquid you need.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot grease until brown.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Baking Temperature: 450°.
Baking Time: 10 to 15 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop stewed tomatoes into large mixing bowl, then add onion, olives, garlic powder and salt to taste.
Mix well.
May be put in the refrigerator overnight to blend all flavors.
Serve with your favorite corn chips.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skin until tender, peel and slice thinly into bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp, remove bacon from pan and cook in the fat until tender the onion.
Then mix in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Stir in gradually water and vinegar. Cook, stirring, until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over potatoes.
Add the crisp bacon, broken into pieces.
Cover and let stand until ready to serve.
Keep hot or heat over hot water.

title: carrot cake
directions: Stir in everything except carrots, pineapple and walnuts. Beat well, then add carrots, walnuts and pineapple to mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use cream cheese and powdered sugar icing.

title: squirrel and dumplings
directions: Pressure cook or boil squirrels until tender.
Save stock. Cook dumplings in squirrel stock.
Add squirrel to dumplings and stock.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
If thickening is needed, use cornstarch and water.
Use your favorite recipe for the dumplings.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Combine cake ingredients and bake at 350°.
Use two 8 inch pans and slice layers to make 4.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Season crawfish tails with salt, cayenne pepper, garlic powder and seasoned salt.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Saute onions, garlic and bell pepper until tender.
Add crawfish tails and cook on low heat 20 to 30 minutes until done.
If you want more gravy, add a little water and thicken with cornstarch.
Just before serving, squeeze lemon juice over dish.
Serve with rice.

title: roladen
directions: Tenderize steaks and lay out flat.
Spread with mustard.
Lay 2 slices bacon and enough pickles to cover half of steak.
Use cooking string or thread and roll up steak to form a log.
Wrap with thread so that the insides won't fall out.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
In large skillet heat the oil and then brown the round steaks until browned evenly.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: peppermint chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix chocolate chips, butter and cream in a heavy saucepan. Place over very low heat and stir until chips and butter are melted and mixture is smooth and thick.
Remove from heat.
Beat in the powdered sugar until mixture is smooth again.
Stir in the peppermint extract.
Cover and chill about 1 or 2 hours, until mixture is thick enough to shape or drop into small candy cups. Divide the mixture into 24 portions.
Drop into paper bonbon cups or first roll into small balls before placing into cups.
(To shape, use a No. 70 or smaller ice cream scoop.
For an extra nice look, roll the shaped, chilled candies in cocoa before serving.)

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Chill.
Place in punch bowl when ready to serve.
Add chilled ginger ale.
Serves 25.

title: pineapple cranberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve juice and add water to make 1 c. liquid).
Heat juice to a boil.
Dissolve Jello in hot liquid. Cool gently, stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partially set (about 30 minutes); keep checking.
Blend pineapple and cranberry sauce together.
Mix well.
Fold into Jello mixture.
Put into serving dish 9 x 9 x 2-inch or a pretty bowl.
Chill until firm.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package, then with mixer beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend cream cheese and Dream Whip together.
Mix very well.
Spread over Jello.
Refrigerate.
Toast pecan in 1 Tbsp. butter at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Let cool and then spread on top of salad.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Boil noodles and put in casserole dish.
Grate both the cheeses together and place on top of noodles.
Melt margarine and pour over cheese.
Mix flour and water together and place on top. Pour milk all over the top and cook at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix chicken broth and soup. Add all bread crumbs and mix.
Add eggs, celery and onion. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour in long baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350° of until done.

title: marinated peas
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add chopped ingredients.
Add all to peas and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Keeps well, up to 5 days.
Cut in half for 1 can of peas.

title: squash and cheese casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water (boiling, salted) until just tender; drain well.
Mix all ingredients except half of cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Place remaining cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until bubbles, cheese melted, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen banana dessert cups(low calorie)
directions: Place bananas, strawberries, pineapple, honey and nutmeg in blender.
Process until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and almonds.
Line 12 muffin cups with foil liners.
Fill with banana mixture.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Blend cherry juice, cornstarch, and sugar in small saucepan.
Cook stirring until boils and thickens.
Cool.

title: extra creamy mayonnaise
directions: Save hard-cooked egg yolk and raw egg yolk; blend well.
Add 1 tablespoonful of oil at a time and beat well with a rotary beater after each addition.
When 1/2 cup of oil has been used, beat in lemon juice and seasonings; add remaining oil, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating with either fork or beater until well blended.
Use as a garnish for mayonnaise.

title: shrimp mold dip
directions: Heat soup and dissolve cream cheese in it.
Mix well using an electric mixer.
Dissolve gelatin in the 1/4 cup cold water and add to hot mixture, mixing well.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease a mold lightly with oil and pour in mixture.
May have to dip mold in hot water to release when ready to serve.
Serves 40 as a spread.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let cook at medium heat; stir until boiling, let boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, instant oats and vanilla.
Stir well.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoons for small cookies.
Also can be placed in buttered oblong pan and cut into squares.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown floured chicken in lard (3 tablespoons).
Remove from stove.
Saute onions, red pepper, green onion, garlic, ham and pork until tender in a large pot with 1 tablespoon lard.
Add broth and water.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Add sausages.
Stir in salt, pepper, red pepper and bay leaves.
Cook for four minutes.
Stir in shrimp and cover.
Cook for 10 more minutes.

title: light cherry cheese coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In batter bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and extract together until smooth.
Carefully unroll French bread dough at seam and place over 15-inch baking stone.
Cut off excess dough that hangs over the side and shape dough into a circle.
Cut a hole in center of dough with 3-inch Cut-N-Seal disc.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello, using only 2 cups of water.
Cool.
Add mashed cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple with juice and chopped nuts. Mix together; chill until congealed.
Great with ham or turkey!

title: cinnamon rolls
