directions: Cut butter into flour and add sugar.
Add enough milk to make dough sticky.
Pour dough out onto floured surface.
Roll out dough to a square and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Roll dough into long tube shape.
Take about 10 inches of string and cut through with string into small cinnamon rolls.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
After rolls cool, top with Confectioners Sugar Icing.

title: beef with peppers(niu jou ch'oa la tzu)
directions: Heat pan; add oil and garlic (crushed).
When garlic turns brown, remove.
Add beef, cut in small thin pieces, and fry a few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add soup stock and continue to cook a few seconds.
(May be made in advance to this point).

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix well.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and water.
Mix well by hand.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Leave in pan and frost while warm.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice onion, zucchini, and potatoes.
Mix the egg and milk together.
Add garlic powder and Mrs. Dash.
Mix well.
Dip the pork chops in the milk-egg mixture coating both sides.
Then, cover with bread crumbs.
Grease glass dish.
Then layer potatoes, zucchini, onion, and pork chops on top.
Add 1/2 C. water to keep potatoes from sticking to pan.
Bake in a 400 degree oven for one hour.

title: cranapple pie
directions: Mix in large bowl apples, cranberry sauce, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Place in pie crust and dot with butter.
Place upper crust on.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 400°.

title: barbecued vegetables
directions: Partially cook beans.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt butter, horseradish mustard, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: 15-minute peanut butter fudge
directions: In
a saucepan, combine sugars, salt and milk.	Cook to 240°. Remove
from
heat	and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat
with a wooden spoon several minutes until thick and
creamy and gloss disappears.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 48 pieces.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Cool and crumble.
Alternate layers of bacon and cheese in pie shell.
Beat eggs, flour, milk, spices and melted butter.
Pour gently over cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375° until brown.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Shake together, then pour over salad.

title: lost bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and cinnamon together.
Dip bread in this mixture and fry on buttered griddle.
Serve with maple syrup or your choice of topping.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 c. warm water in large mixing bowl. Stir in honey, shortening, salt, 1 3/4 c. warm water and the whole wheat flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough all purpose flour to make dough easy to handle.

Turn dough on lightly-floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes). Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up; cover and let rise in warm place until dough doubles (about 1 hour).
Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.
Punch down dough; divide into halves.
Flatten each half with hands or rolling pin into rectangle 18 X 9 inches.
Fold crosswise into thirds, overlapping the 2 sides.
Roll up lightly, beginning at one of the open ends. Press with thumbs to seal after each turn.
Punch edge firmly to seal.
Press each end with sides of hand to seal.
Fold ends under loaf.
Place loaves, seam-sides down, in 2 greased loaf pans (9 X 5 or 8 1/2 X 4 1/2).
Brush with margarine; sprinkle whole wheat flour or crushed oats if desired.
Let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake until loaves are deep golden brown and sound hollow when tapped (40 to 45 minutes).
Remove from pans; cool on wire rack.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: escalloped seafood
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Put layer of crumbs on casserole bottom.
Cover with seafood alternately with crumbs, ending with crumbs.
Pour on evaporated milk.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Combine salt, tomato sauce and paste, parsley and basil with beef.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan, eggs and pepper.
Layer half beef mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with half noodles, then half cottage cheese mixture, then half Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and bake until cheese starts to brown, approximately 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set for 15 minutes.
Do not mix beef tomato mixture with cottage cheese mixture.

title: chimichangas
directions: Brown meat, onion, pepper and garlic in hot oil; drain well. Stir in chili sauce and salt.
Simmer for 1 minute.
Stir in refried beans and cheese.
Remove from heat.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs; add vinegar, vanilla and salt.
Add coconut.
Pour
into deep dish pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add raisins and nuts. Heat applesauce.
In a separate bowl blend eggs, sugar and butter. Add flour mixture to sugar mixture then applesauce (alternately). Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Enjoy!

title: easy cake
directions: Mix cake mix with stick of butter by hand.
Add nuts and place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour over pie filling and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: football chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large saucepan or skillet.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and seasoning mix.
Pour into extra large saucepan.
Add tomato paste and water.
simmer 30 minutes. Stirring occasionally, add beans and continue cooking on simmer another 15 minutes.
Feed the crowd or place in airtight containers and freeze for later use.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Melt margarine; dip fish to coat, then roll in mixture made of stuffing, cheese and parsley.
Place flat in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: curried baked fruit
directions: Thoroughly drain fruit and arrange in an 8 x 11 1/2-inch (2-quart) casserole.
Melt butter and mix with sugar and curry. Pour over fruit and bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In small saucepan, add oil, garlic, salt and red pepper flakes. Cook over low heat until garlic is lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Meanwhile, in large saucepot, add enough water to come halfway up side.
Bring to a boil.
Add broccoli.
Cook 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain.
Rinse under cold water; drain again. Place broccoli in medium bowl, combine lemon juice and oil.
Pour over broccoli and toss well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: strawberry dessert soup
directions: Puree strawberries in a blender until they are smooth.
Pour into saucepan.
Add water, sugar, tapioca and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove form heat. Add lemon juice.
Chill.
Before serving, stir in orange and grapefruit.
Serve cold.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat at least 15 minutes.

title: crunchy cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in next five ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix jello as directed.
When jello begins to set, stir in drained pineapple and sliced bananas.
Add marshmallows.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 tablespoons pineapple juice; spread on top of jello.
Let set for 1 hour or until jello sets up. (Substitute low-fat cream cheese.)
This makes a great low-fat dessert.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Mix zucchini, onions, green peppers and garlic; cover with cracked ice and sprinkle with 1/2 cup of salt.
Mix again; let stand 3 hours.
Drain and rinse well.

title: broccoli and cauliflower toss
directions: Remove leaves of cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Set aside. Remove stalks from broccoli and separate into flowerets. Combine cauliflower, broccoli and onion. Toss gently.

title: hot avocado appetizer
directions: Cut avocados in half lengthwise, separate and remove seed. Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in top of double boiler and heat until sauce is smooth, stirring constantly.
Spoon hot sauce into halves and serve as an appetizer or cut avocado into cubes and serve with toothpicks to dip in sauce as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: irish cream liqueur cake
directions: Melt ingredients in a saucepan set over low heat.
Keep warm until ready to use.

title: calico broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Heat until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Mix together browned meat and Ragu; simmer.
Bring water to boil, add noodles and oil; cook until limp but not completely done.
Rinse in cold water.

title: open house punch
directions: Place all frozen ingredients into a large punch bowl.
Add the fruit punch.
Pour the ginger ale over the sherbet and let foam. Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: rice and pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides; reserve drippings.
Combine mushroom soup, water and rice until it boils.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: All ingredients are raw.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into an unbaked pie shell (large one).
Cook for about 1 hour in 325° to 350° oven.
Good served warm or chill and top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: swedish nut cookies
directions: Beat margarine, butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla together with a beater.
Add flour, then refrigerate for awhile.
Roll into small balls (walnut size) and flatten with bottom of floured glass.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until edges are slightly brown.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Cheesecake pan is required.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for several hours.
Use as a dip for raw cauliflower, zucchini, celery, carrots, raw mushrooms, etc.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Mix crackers, salmon, onion, egg and half of milk.
Place in baking dish.
Add peppers, melted butter and milk over all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix altogether except pecans.
Add pecans last.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Heat oven to 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° when you put pie in.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Place partially cooked broccoli in a baking dish.
Then add chicken on top.
In a bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins in small bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain and reserve.
Preheat oven to moderate 350°.

title: coconut and oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in casserole.
Saute almonds and Ritz crackers in margarine and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to directions on box.
Melt cheese in microwave.
Saute mushrooms and onion together.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Add Worcestershire sauce and mustard to tomato paste.
Blend well.
Combine beef, onion, rice, salt and the sauce mixture.
Cut tops off peppers.
Remove seeds and spoon mixture into peppers. Bake for 40 minutes or until done.

title: ham and asparagus fettuccine
directions: If you're watching your sodium, substitute reduced sodium ham for the regular ham.
It will reduce the total sodium content by about 1/4.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Mix together and fold in 1 stiffly beaten egg white.
Cut fish into 2 or 3-inch cubes.
Dip in mix and deep fry.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in square baking dish (sprayed with Pam). Sprinkle dry soup mix evenly on top.
Pour 1 1/2 cups water over chicken breasts. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered. (Baste frequently with juices.)

title: tossed chicken salad
directions: Combine all but the noodles and chill.
Add the can
of noodles just before serving.
Serves 10.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic. Drain.
Add 2 cans tomato sauce and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: easy feta chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with 1 tablespoon of the lemon juice.
Season with salt and black pepper.
Top with Feta cheese and drizzle with remaining tablespoon lemon juice.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Sprinkle with red pepper and parsley.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, butter, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients together and mix into creamed mixture. Form small balls and roll in the 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ella's chocolate nut pie
directions: Mix all together as listed.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Slice one tube of cookie dough and place slices in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press together to form a solid layer.
Mix cheese, eggs, sugar, and vanilla.
Pour onto pressed dough.
Slice second tube of cookies and place slices close together on top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch buttered casserole dish, place alternate layers of onions, chips and cheese.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over layers.
Sprinkle cayenne pepper over the top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add onions and celery. Cook until done.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into casserole and top with reserved noodles. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer as follows:
bread, cheese, bacon, mushrooms.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper, milk and pour over mixture.
Bake covered 45 minutes, then uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chef salad
directions: Place lettuce into 2 individual bowls.
Arrange ham strips, Swiss cheese, cucumber, Blue cheese and hard-boiled eggs on top of lettuce in each salad bowl.

title: spinach filled baked potatoes
directions: Split each potato lengthwise down the center after baking and carefully scoop out inside, leaving the potato skin shell.
Set shells aside.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs, flour, salt, soda and bananas and mix thoroughly.
Stir in walnuts last.
Bake in greased cake pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix crushed cookies and melted oleo into 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread softened ice cream over cookie crust.
Spread fudge topping over ice cream.

title: oysterette munchies
directions: In medium bowl, whisk together oil, dill, garlic, salt, lemon pepper and dressing mix.
Put crackers in a large flat pan.
Pour the herb mixture over them.
With a spatula, turn and mix the crackers well, coating the crackers.
Let them stand at room temperature for 1 hour, turning every 10 minutes.

title: coconut cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add lemon peel and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: beef rice casserole
directions: Brown beef, add rice, soup, water, salt, celery and green peppers.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in a greased casserole (2-quart). Cover and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mountain soup
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat; mix all ingredients with desired amount of water and cook on low until done.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chili casserole
directions: Bake in preheated 400° oven 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
You may need to drain a little grease off or place dish on cookie sheet.

title: hilton head chicken
directions: Line casserole dish with dried beef.
Wrap skinned, deboned chicken breast with bacon; salt and pepper.
Mix cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups together; pour over chicken breasts. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts(2 variations of recipe)
directions: Precook noodles. Place cubed chicken in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish; layer with Swiss cheese and layer of noodles. Pour soup and wine over mixture; sprinkle with stuffing mix, combined with margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: chocolate-peanut butter candy
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar, butter and peanut butter and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan for thick candy or larger pan for thinner candy.
Slowly melt chocolate in double boiler (can be microwaved).
Pour chocolate over crumb mixture.
Let harden and cut into squares.

title: mock peanut butter cups
directions: *Or use sweet chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons shortening.

title: meatball subs
directions: Soak bread slices in enough evaporated milk to saturate.
Mix all ingredients together using just enough bread crumbs to form. Roll into 2-inch meat balls.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with Ragu spaghetti sauce and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Place 3 or 4 meatballs on Italian rolls. Add sauce and shredded Mozzarella if desired.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs and add bread, milk, cheese, mustard, salt and drained sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dressed up chicken
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Lay chicken in bottom of dish. Mix preserves, soup mix and dressing; pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover.
If using boneless chicken, reduce baking time to 40 minutes.
Sauce is good over rice or noodles.

title: slush(frozen drink)
directions: Steep tea bags in 2 cups boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in container that may be frozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place cubed bread in bottom of greased casserole, top with grated cheese.
Brown sausage and cut each into thirds.
Drain and place on cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and dry mustard. Pour over other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
In morning, dilute mushroom soup with milk and pour over casserole, bake at 300° in 8 x 12-inch pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta garden salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package: drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Run cold tap water over vegetables in strainer to thaw completely;
drain.
Combine pasta, vegetables, olives, and cheese in a large bowl.
Add salad dressing as needed, about 1 1/2 cups.
Toss.
Chill 2 hours.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: waldorf-astoria cake
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda and mix well.
Now add salad dressing, water and vanilla. Bake in loaf pan or layer cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: raisin carrot muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger. Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Separately combine, pineapple, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Add this to dry ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Use greased or paper-lined cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: super cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until soft.
Add sugar slowly.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Add flour, juice, vanilla and salt, then sour cream; beat well.
Bake in buttered spring-form or 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until top is browned to satisfaction.
Add fruit filling on top when cooled, if desired.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown chicken lightly in oil. Add water, wine, soup and broccoli. Bring to a boil, separating broccoli. Stir in rice; cover. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter, pecans and 1 egg.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix together 2 eggs, cream cheese and box of sugar.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cake mixture and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Melt butter and add onion soup mix.
Can mix in a small amount of garlic powder if desired.
Stir well.
Pour mixture over broken pretzels and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250°.
Bake 10 minutes, then stir.
Bake another 10 minutes, then stir.
Bake 20 minutes and stir when removed from oven.
Remove pretzels from tray and place in container.

title: cranberry upside down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to measure 1 1/4 cups; set aside.
Pour butter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cranberries, and walnuts.
Top with pineapple.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In
large
saucepan combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt. Cook
over	high
heat about 5 minutes.
Stir often and scrape the bottom of pan.
Mixture will form up; add butter or margarine
and pecans.
Over
medium
heat, continue cooking, stirring bottom and
sides	of
pan, until candy reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool about 2 minutes.
Beat with spoon until thick and creamy.
Drop from tablespoon onto sheet of paper; let cool. Makes about 20.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour a shallow square pan.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar together until thoroughly blended.
Add egg; beat until thoroughly blended.
In a small bowl, combine applesauce and raisins.
Add dry ingredients and applesauce-raisin mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into prepared baking dish for 12 to 13 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Crumble and set aside. In the drippings, saute onion and green pepper until tender. Beat eggs and milk in large bowl. Stir in hash browns, cheese, salt, pepper, dill, onion, green pepper and bacon. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Toss all ingredients lightly together.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: mom's beer muffins
directions: Mix together and spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.
Makes about 12 muffins.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add sugar, oil, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and prunes.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan which has been greased.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to an hour.
Cool slightly.
Pierce cake with a fork and pour topping into cake.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Steam broccoli, carrots, cauliflower and celery until crisp-tender. Cool. Combine steamed vegetables, green pepper and green onion.
Combine apple juice, vinegar and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and mix well. Refrigerate overnight. Will keep up to 3 days.

title: brown rice
directions: Put dry rice in a casserole that has been sprayed with Pam. Saute the margarine and onion in a skillet until mixture is transparent.
Pour the beef consomme over the dry rice.
Add boiling water to the empty consomme can and dissolve 2 beef bouillon cubes in it.
When dissolved, pour over the rice and mix together.
Bake at 350° or 400° until all liquid is cooked out of rice, about 30 minutes.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 quart hot water; dissolve and add cold water.
Mix sugar with 1 quart hot water; dissolve and add cold water.
Add to juice and water.
Freeze.
Thaw to slush or for 2 to 3 days or month in advance.
Take out to slush; add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Mix all except bean threads and chill.
Before serving, mix salad with bean threads and salad dressing.

title: copie's baked corn
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with butter or margarine. Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Mix corn and milk together. Add beaten eggs, cornstarch and sugar mixture all in a bowl.
Pour into a casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour. Very good.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse in cold water and drain.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: charlotte russe
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/3 cup boiling water*.
Cool.
Beat egg yolks; add sugar.
Whip whipping cream and add vanilla.
Beat egg whites.
Mix egg yellows and gelatin.
Add whipped cream and egg whites.
Taste to see if sweet enough; add more sherry if needed. Pour into ladyfinger-lined bowl.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 3 cups cold water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in a mold to congeal. Serves 16.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all the ingredients with electric mixer for about five minutes.
Bake in a casserole dish at 375° for 1 hour.

title: eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk; stir until smooth. Beat in Cool Whip; set aside. Line a 13 x 9-inch dish with crackers.
Spread 1/2 pudding on crackers. Place another layer of crackers on top of pudding. Layer remaining pudding on top of graham crackers. Place another layer of crackers on top.
Prepare frosting as directed on package and spread on top.
Chill. Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: kabob marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over beef or chicken.
Allow to marinate overnight for best results.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli, chicken mixture (items 2 to 5) and bread crumbs.
Bake in greased, uncovered, dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Add sour cream and flavoring; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300° to 325°.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender, drain and rinse in cold water. Chop and add vegetables.
Combine and toss all ingredients.
Let marinate overnight for best flavor.

title: seafood rice jambalaya
directions: Put all ingredients, except oleo, in rice cooker.
Mix well. Place oleo on top.
Cook until bell chimes.

title: chocolate, chocolate, chocolate cake
directions: Grease three 8-inch round cake pans.
Dust with cocoa.
Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar together until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mix, blending thoroughly, beginning and ending with flour.
Thoroughly blend in melted chocolate.
Pour half of batter into the 3 pans; sprinkle the fudge pieces evenly over the batter and pour the remaining batter over the fudge pieces in the 3 pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until tester comes clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then turn out on rack to cool.
Frosting recipe follows.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix berries with 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Mix remaining sugar, flour and milk.
Preheat oven to 350.
Melt butter in 9 inch square pan.
Drop flour mixture into pan.
Top with berries. Bake for 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all together in freezer can and freeze as usual.
I've tried this with crushed pineapple and Sprite!
Doris.

title: broccoli and herbs
directions: In microwave, cook broccoli in packages (remove outer wrapper and puncture carton several times) on High for 7 minutes.
Drain and place in a covered 2-quart casserole.

title: chicken-mushroom saute
directions: Brown chicken in butter and oil in large skillet until golden. Remove and set aside.
Saute mushrooms and onions in drippings for 2 minutes.
Add chicken, skin side up; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add wine, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve at once over rice or noodles or refrigerate or freeze.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine tuna, crumbs, celery, cheese and relish.
Add mustard and lemon juice to mayonnaise; stir into tuna.
Form into patties and broil 5 minutes on each side.
Serve in hamburger buns.
Makes 4 large or 6 medium sandwiches.

title: pie crust - makes 5
directions: Mix Crisco and flour until like meal.
Beat egg.
Add vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Evenly roll out.
Divide to freeze or put into aluminum pans.

title: old-fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add margarine, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir and dissolve jello, sugar and hot water.
Place into refrigerator until firm.
Add pecans, pineapple, apple, orange and cranberries.
Spray Pam on ring mold.
Pour in mold and store in refrigerator.

title: apple salad
directions: Chop apples.
Put in bowl and mix with whipped cream.

title: ella's divinity fudge
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water; place in boiler over slow heat.
Stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add syrup slowly, still beating.
Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture thickens.
Add nuts, coconut and colored cherries (optional).

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet onion bake
directions: Saute onions in butter. Cook rice in water for 5 minutes. Drain and mix with onions.
Add cheese, half and half and pepper. Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 hour.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk.
Stir well.
Set aside. Combine cheese, flour, salt,
paprika and pepper; mix well. Rinse chicken and pat dry. Dip in egg mixture and dredge in flour mixture.
Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, peanut butter and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix ingredients with hands until forms a ball.
Pat out flat on 9 x 13-inch ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes, until light brown around edges.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sweet potato custard pie
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash with margarine.
Beat in sugar, flour, vanilla and lemon extract. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk; beat well.
Pour filling in pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet, break up and brown sausage.
Add onion in the last few minutes; cook until clear.
Add rice, broth and water.
Stir in salt; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat to low. Cook for 30 minutes, or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Layer shrimp and onions, crushing bay leaves and cloves over each layer.
Pour oil mixture over shrimp.
Marinate for 24 hours, turning after 12 hours.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix sour cream, 1/2 cup cheese, chives, salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir margarine into hot noodles; stir in sour cream mixture.
Arrange on warm platter; sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.

title: cock-a-leekie soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, melt butter and saute leeks, potatoes and onion, stirring often, until onion is tender.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in stock and milk; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove and puree vegetables.
Return vegetables to soup; add cream and season with salt and pepper. Warm and serve garnished with chives.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain and add tomato sauce.
Cook the lasagna as directed on box.
In a
9 x 13-inch dish, layer three times the lasagna, beef and cheese. Top the last layer with extra cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: auld lang syne casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients
together	except	cornflakes
and margarine in a
casserole.	Cover with cornflakes;	drizzle on margarine.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: *Use nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon and cloves, in that order.

title: brandy whipped cream sauce(for reagan's persimmon pudding)
directions: Beat egg until light and fluffy.
Beat in melted butter, powdered sugar, salt and brandy flavoring.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Gently fold into the first mixture.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Stir before spooning on pudding.

title: supper omelet(micro magic)
directions: Shred potatoes, rinse thoroughly and drain well, then mix with onion in a micro-safe 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes, stirring once, until potatoes are tender.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; beat well.
Now add green pepper and tomato and pour all over the potatoes.
Mix lightly, cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir to move cooked edges to the center.
Cover and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes until center is almost set, rotating dish once and sprinkling cheese at rotation time.
Let stand a few minutes. Cut into wedges, serve and enjoy.

title: bacon wrapped bread sticks
directions: Cut bacon or turkey bacon slices into thirds.
Wrap bacon around bread stick and cook in microwave.
Check after 5 or 6 minutes to see if bacon is crisp.
If not, continue to microwave until crisp.
Remove bread sticks from microwave and roll in Parmesan cheese.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Combine cake mix, melted butter and egg. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Place the marshmallows on top and return to oven about 3 minutes or until marshmallows puff up. Melt the chips, syrup and butter. Add vanilla. Pour this over the peanuts and Rice Krispies. Then spread over marshmallows. Refrigerate, then cut into bars.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as box directions.
Mix with cooked broccoli, soup, milk and other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in covered casserole dish.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Sift flour with salt. Cut shortening into flour. Beat the egg with 5 tablespoons water. Add to flour mixture.
Use remainder of water, if necessary.
Makes 3 pie shells.

title: grandma's cottage cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, flour and eggs; beat smooth.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nutmeg with lemon juice.
Turn into crust.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown potato stuffing for peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers and remove seeds.
Saute meat, onion and garlic; drain.
Add seasonings and potato and cook until potatoes are thawed.
Add egg and mix.
Spoon mixture into peppers.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour juice over peppers.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°, until peppers are tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form all ingredients into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Top with cherry.
Freezes well.

title: dutch crumb cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cinnamon and egg until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Dissolve baking soda in milk and add to crumbled mixture, stirring until blended.
Grease a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Put batter in pan and add reserved crumbs for topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then the mix, then crackers and then mix.
Top with crackers.
Soften frosting in microwave.
Pour over crackers. Let set overnight.

title: eight layer dip
directions: On about a 12 to 14-inch serving plate or platter, spread bean dip to about 3/8-inch thickness.
Carefully spread avocado dip on bean dip to within 3/4 inch of edges.
Spoon sour cream on avocado dip to within 3/4 inch of previous edge.
Continue layering Cheddar cheese, Brick cheese, onions, tomato and finish in the center with olives.
Cover and chill.

title: grady's cheese log
directions: Grind in food chopper the pecans and garlic and all hard cheese. Mix with salad dressing and cream cheese (best by hand). Roll into logs and roll logs in paprika. Let cool and set back and enjoy.

title: mint danties(wedding or christmas according to color and shape.)
directions: Stir margarine, Karo and 1/2 of the sugar in pan and boil until bubbly. Remove and add rest of sugar.
Knead until smooth. Any flavoring can be added such as mint, anise, butternut, etc. Add flavoring before kneading.
Shape as desired.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large skillet, cook meat and garlic until meat is no longer pink; drain off fat.
Stir in drained pinto beans, taco sauce and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: angel rolls
directions: Mix all
ingredients well and put into ungreased muffin tins. Fill about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: surprise hash browns
directions: Mix together sour cream, salt, pepper, cream of celery soup, Cheddar soup and milk.
Stir in onions and potatoes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter; add salt, pepper, chicken, undiluted soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Drain noodles.
Arrange in layers with chicken mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.
Add chicken broth if mixture is too thick.

title: steak casserole
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Layer vegetables and steak in greased dish.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and then press down with fork.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Slice strawberries and mix with glaze. Pour in graham cracker crust. Top with cool whip. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: tortellini stew
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add tortellini and onion and brown over high heat, stirring often, 1 to 2 minutes, until tortellini is nicely browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice, green beans, mushrooms, potato, parsnip, corn, garlic, basil, salt and pepper. Cover and cook for 10 minutes or until veggies are crisp-tender.

title: charles' chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; let cool.
Saute onions, celery and green peppers in a large skillet with margarine.
Add Velveeta and soups; do not add water!
Let simmer on low.
Boil spaghetti.
Bone chicken and add to soup mixture.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: strawberry-banana pie
directions: Cook sweetened strawberries over low heat.
Mix flour with water; stir in boiling strawberries.
Bake 2 pie shells.
Slice bananas and cover bottom of shell.
Add strawberries, then top with cream cheese mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Combine mashed potato and egg yolk, stirring until well blended.
Stir in cheese, green pepper, green onions and celery salt.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) at high speed of an electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Gently fold egg whites into potato mixture.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Sprinkle paprika evenly over top of casserole and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: simple simon tuna pie
directions: Arrange border of cooked noodles in a greased dish.
Center with tuna fish and sprinkle with onion and egg.
Blend soup, sauce, salt and pepper and pour over fish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: squash patties(good)
directions: Mix together. Spoon in hot grease like patties, turning often. Drain.

title: caramel frosting
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, heat together butter and brown sugar over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts.
Blend in milk and cool.
Gradually beat in sugar until spreading consistency. Add milk.
Frost 13 x 9-inch loaf pan.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Mix well. Pour into three 8-inch cake pans and bake about 35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on wire racks. For a moister cake, freeze before icing.

title: cheesy rice
directions: Bring milk, water, margarine and salt to boil in medium saucepan.
Add 4 slices of the cheese; stir until completely melted.
Return to boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Garnish with remaining 2 cheese slices.

title: candy cake
directions: Sift together, flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together, shortening and sugar, added gradually.
Beat in one egg, continue beating 1 minute.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla; add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mix.
Fold in marshmallows and chocolate bits.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine butter, brown sugar, nuts; sprinkle over batter and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve from pan with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until limp.
Place onion in saucepan with carrots, celery and chicken broth; cover and simmer 15 minutes. Transfer mixture to blender; add salt and pepper.
Cover and whirl a few seconds.
Add the half and half or milk; blend again until smooth.
Reheat soup, but do not boil.
May also be chilled and served cold.
Good served in mugs.
Serves 4.

title: wild rice oven pilaf
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish combine boiling water and margarine or butter.
Stir until melted.
Stir in brown rice, wild rice, onion, salt and pepper. Cover.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in carrot and frozen peas.
Cover and bake 10 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Makes 4 to 6 side-dish servings.

title: chicken supreme(ham, veal or turkey)
directions: Add onions, carrots, bay leaf, peppercorns and parsley to the broth.
Simmer for 10 minutes; strain.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan; stir in the flour.
Add the first mixture slowly, stirring all the while, then cook, stirring until smooth.
Add the cream; cook until thickened, then fold in the chicken and eggs. Heat thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve in rice ring.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 14-inch pan (floured and greased).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter mousse pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, jelly and milk with mixer on medium speed until well blended. Fold in Cool Whip. Mix well. Pour into Oreo crust. Freeze overnight.

title: eclair cake
directions: Beat milk and pudding until thick.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Place a layer of graham crackers in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Pour mixture over crackers.
Add another layer gently over the pudding, forming the top of the cake.
Spread icing on these crackers.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese on the last 1/2 hour and cover.

title: jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese and stir.
Add drained fruit and stir again.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill before serving. If salad seems a little dry, add more Cool Whip.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, chilies and onions to your taste in a pan and heat.
Grate cheese and set aside.
Dip tortillas in hot grease; place on paper towels and blot.
Place some of soup mixture on bottom of pan to prevent sticking.
Put some of mixture in tortillas and roll.
Pour remaining on top along with cheese. Put in oven at 350° and heat until onion is done.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: divine date nut loaf
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, dates and pecan halves.
Mix well together.
Pour into greased and floured pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Place in cold oven.
Turn to 300° and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until firm in the middle.
Cool before removing from pan.
Use very sharp knife to slice.
Wrap in foil.
Freezes well.

title: joni's seasoned roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
In an iron skillet, place roast and prepare in the following manner.

title: no shortening pineapple cake and cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together flour and sugar; add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely before topping.
Serve topped with fresh, canned or frozen fruit, confectioners sugar or cream cheese frosting.

title: chicken with cashews
directions: Heat wok.
Add oil, heat and add ginger and garlic.
Stir-fry for 1 minute, then add chicken and stir for another two minutes until chicken begins to turn white.
Add celery and stir for another minute.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream together.
Stir in dry Jell-O. Fold in oranges or pineapple.
Add pecans and marshmallows.
Chill before serving.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat above ingredients 20 minutes (mixer only).
Then add 1 tablespoon celery seed and 2/3 cup vinegar.
Beat into mixture lightly.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Boil berries for 10 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Cook additional 3 minutes.
Place in shallow pan overnight.
In the morning, heat and put in jars and freeze.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cook
carrots in enough water to cover them until crisp and tender,
about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add carrots.
Sprinkle sugar and nutmeg.
Cook, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.

title: overnight orange french toast
directions: Place bread in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, orange juice, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Pour over bread slices; turn slices to coat evenly.
Sprinkle with a little grated orange rind.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet and sour chicken chunks
directions: Bake chicken chunks according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, bring 1 cup water to boiling. Stir in rice.
Remove pan from heat.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: savory brussels sprouts
directions: In covered saucepan, heat Brussels sprouts, water and bouillon to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook 5 minutes.
Add onion rings; cook, uncovered, until onions are tender, about 5 minutes more.
Makes 3 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spread thawed hash browns in greased pan.
Mix 1/2 cup melted margarine, cheese, sour cream and soup.
Pour and spread on top of potatoes.
Top with cracker crumbs and drizzle other 1/2 cup of melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato lasagne
directions: Clean, cut and boil potatoes.
Mash potatoes, adding milk and margarine to consistency desired.
Cook lasagne noodles; drain. Saute onions in butter; drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer noodles, potatoes, onions and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg.
Add taco mix.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream with taco mix.
In glass pan, layer cream cheese mixture, browned meat, peppers, onions, tomatoes and lettuce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, margarine, milk and egg.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Arrange over batter, sliced peaches.
Save juice.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and peach juice at medium speed.
Spoon over top of peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate when cool.
Use pie pan.
Can double recipe in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: cool lemon drop cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar; coat.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cream together sugars and butter.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Blend in egg/raisin mixture, oatmeal and nuts.
Dough will be very stiff.
Roll into small balls and flatten slightly.
On an ungreased cookie sheet, bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Chop oranges in food processor or blender.
Combine with cranberries and sugar in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: easy skillet pork chops
directions: Saute pork chops in oleo until brown; set aside.
Reserve drippings.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Add salt, pepper, cornstarch and mustard; stir well.
Add water, bouillon and Worcestershire.
Stir until bouillon is dissolved.
Place pork chops in skillet.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients except cherries.
Pour over melted butter.
Drop spoonfuls of cherries on the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: potato gratin
directions: Place onion and garlic clove in a large saucepan with milk, cream and bay leaf.
Slowly bring to boiling point and immediately remove from heat.
Let cool for 30 minutes.
Discard clove of garlic and bay leaf.
Season.
Thickly slice potatoes.
Add to milk and bring to a boil, then remove immediately from heat.
Using a draining spoon, transfer potato slices to a large shallow ovenproof dish.
Pour milk over and sprinkle with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Cover chicken with next 3 ingredients.
Add water if necessary. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Drain pineapple.
Add during last 10 minutes of baking.

title: meringue
directions: Cook ingredients to thread stage (232°).
Gradually pour this over 2 stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until mixture holds stiff peaks.
Add 1/4 teaspoon almond extract.

title: artichoke heart ball
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients, blending well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape mixture into small, round
balls.
Roll in bread crumbs and place on cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Thoroughly wash oysters in shells in cold water; open each with oyster knife.
Discard flat upper shells, wash deep bottom shells. Place each oyster in shell half.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, thyme and pepper; toss with melted butter.
Top each oyster with about 1 teaspoon of crumb mixture.
Arrange shells on bed of rock salt in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix apricot jam, Russian dressing and dry onion soup mix together.
Dip wings into sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Slice strawberries.
Add sugar and 1 bottle of wine, sparkling water and rum.
Serve very cold.
Serves 20.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Add melted margarine and 2/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook and drain broccoli well.
Mix all ingredients and add to Jiffy mix.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: ham roll-up cheese ball
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Turn out onto cupboard; knead until completely blended.
Divide into 3 equal parts.
Roll in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Will stay fresh for 5 to 7 days.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender on high.
Count to 10.
Put into a large greased tin pie pan.
Just before putting into oven, sprinkle a little nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except stuffing) and pour into baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour or until top is browned.

title: cream cheese stuffed celery
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and stuff celery with mixture.

title: lemon bars
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a bowl and blend well like a pie crust.
Put into a 14 x 10-inch baking pan and press firmly on bottom of pan.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: bean bake
directions: Cook separately lima beans and green beans; drain. Combine cooked beans and mushroom soup, milk and water chestnuts.
Bake in a casserole 25 minutes at 375°.
Crumble French onion rings on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Brush over warm biscuits before removing from baking sheet.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, chili sauce, egg, salt and pepper, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Shape beef mixture to form an 8 x 4 1/2-inch loaf.
Place on rack in open roasting pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until no longer pink and juices run clear.
Delicious when served with creamed potatoes and brown gravy.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Mix last three ingredients in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water and milk.
Add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef
and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: "cream soda without a fountain"
directions: Beat egg whites well.
Combine all ingredients (except soda and tartartic acid).
Place over gentle fire, stirring well for about 30 minutes.
Remove from fire and strain.
Divide into two parts in two bottles or jars.
Into one bottle add soda, into other bottle add tartaric acid; shake each well.
When cold, they are ready to use by pouring 3 to 4 spoonfuls from both parts into separate glasses, each filled 1/3 full with water.
Stir each and only then pour them together.

title: creamy carrot potato boats
directions: Bake potatoes in a 375° oven about 45 minutes or until tender. Cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
In a small mixer bowl combine potato pulp, carrot, cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and pepper.
Beat until smooth, adding more milk, if necessary.
Stir in green onions.
Spoon potato mixture into potato shells.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until heated through.

title: chunky joe's cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Place cake mix, eggs, butter, brown sugar and vanilla in a large bowl.
Stir with a spoon or blender.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Cookies will be puffy.
Let cool on pan 2 minutes, then remove to wire rack to finish cooling.

title: mom's corn cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into loaf pan, 9 x 5. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until all liquid is absorbed.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, dry mustard, salt and onion.
Add vinegar and oil alternately, a small amount at a time, beginning with vinegar. Beat well.
Stir in celery seed and paprika.
Store, covered in refrigerator.
Serve on fresh fruit or vegetable salads.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown beef; stir and drain.
Mix in medium bowl the mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve quiche with fruit-melons, strawberries, pineapple, grapes, cooked broccoli or a vegetable salad.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with fresh vegetables, carrot sticks, etc.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put mushroom and celery soup in casserole dish.
Add water and 1/2 of dry soup.
Put in chicken and rest of dry soup on top. Bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
I usually cover with foil, but it might not be necessary.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook together cornstarch, sugar, jello and boiling water until thick.
Let cool.
Mix with strawberries and pour into baked pie shell.
Let stand 3 or 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Beat well and add eggs, one at a time.
Then add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch greased pan in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: green peppers, tomatoes and onion(portuguese)
directions: Heat oil in skillet with garlic.
Wash and cut up peppers the long way; slice onion heavy.
Saute a few minutes in skillet.
Add red peppers, tomatoes and salt.
Cook, covered, for 2 minutes or until done.

title: pig licken' good cake
directions: Mix ingredients in cake. Mix and bake as instructed on box. Cool cake.

title: lo-cal onion dip
directions: Put in a blender on low (except peppers).
Mix about 1 minute. Stir in peppers.
Serve cold.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Partially thaw broccoli under running water.
Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onion; saute for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon; heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Add noodles and salt; continue to boil.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder; cook for 4 minutes.
Add milk, cheese and pepper.
Continue cooking over medium heat, until cheese is melted and broccoli is tender. Serves 12.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer wafer crumbs and pack in.
Add chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts and coconut last.
Drizzle canned milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kim's picante sauce
directions: Cook slowly in large Dutch oven for 4 to 5 hours.

title: yummy candied yams
directions: Combine
all
ingredients, except potatoes, in saucepan and cook
about 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.	Place sliced potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy flank steak
directions: Pierce steak all over with a fork.
Combine all ingredients and pour over steak.
Marinate overnight.
Broil, slice thin and serve.
(The remaining marinade can be heated up and used as a gravy.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions (don't overcook). Saute chopped celery in butter. Add cream of mushroom soup and sour cream. Simmer until thoroughly mixed. Spread small amount of sauce in bottom of casserole dish and alternate layers of sauce and broccoli, beginning and ending with sauce. Bake at 350° for 3 minutes. Add grated cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Chop up chicken.
Mix all together except almonds and chips. Put in baking dish. Sprinkle almonds on top, then potato chips. Bake at 450° for 14 minutes.
May be frozen.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt caramels and milk into a double boiler or microwave, then add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased pan or buttered wax paper.
Cool completely, about 5 hours.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler or microwave.
Dip each piece of candy into chocolate and put on buttered platter to cool.

title: swedish apple pie(portuguese)
directions: Melt butter and let cool.
Dice apples in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Beat in separate bowl the egg, flour, sugar and melted butter.
Pour over apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add bananas and mash.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift dry ingredients. Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Marinate vermicelli overnight in Accent, Lawry's salt, lemon juice and cooking oil.
Next day, mix other ingredients, toss, let stand several hours or overnight.
Makes a lot.
Mix vermicelli with hands.

title: portuguese kale soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
In the morning, drain; add the onion, sausage (cut in pieces), kale (broken in pieces), salt, pepper, vinegar and 10 cups water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cook gently 2 to 3 hours.
Add potatoes and 1 additional cup water.
Continue cooking until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Chop the livers and gizzards.
In a large saucepan (5-quart), combine livers, gizzards and chicken backs.
Cover with water. Bring to a rolling boil. Reduce heat and simmer until meat comes off bones.
Remove bones.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice. Bring to a boil and add rice.
Cook until rice is done.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a quart pan, combine water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Add macaroni slowly. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 8 to 9 minutes.
Drain macaroni and place in casserole.
Stir in margarine, egg, salt and dry mustard.
Add 2 1/2 cups grated cheese and mix well.
Pour milk over the mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 to 12 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Rub
outside
of
tenderloin with Italian seasoning and cook in a 12-inch Dutch oven for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Make walnut size balls.
Press flat with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: excellent dip
directions: Blend well and chill.

title: veal marsala
directions: Pound veal between pieces of waxed paper.
Coat veal with flour.
Heat butter in skillet until it sizzles.
Add veal and cook over high heat until brown on both sides.
Add mushrooms and saute briefly.
Add bouillon and Marsala and stir together for 1 minute.
Arrange veal on hot plate.
Pour pan juice over.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pizza
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Cut potatoes and onion into wedges and place on top of chicken and between chicken.
Season tomato sauce with oregano and garlic powder. Pour over chicken. Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix, chill and eat.

title: stuffed hamburger
directions: Prepare stuffing.
Combine milk and meat; divide into 5 patties.
On wax paper, pat each to 6-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each patty.
Draw meat over stuffing; cover all stuffing.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pork chops in barbecue sauce
directions: Brown pork chops and drain off fat.
Combine sauce ingredients and pour over meat.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix together first 5 dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Combine egg and orange juice and add to dry ingredients.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: whoopie pies and filling
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs and egg yolks.
Add some milk and all dry ingredients; add mix.
Then add hot water and mix.
Drop by even teaspoons on a cookie sheet so they will be even in size. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix the butter with crackers and sugar.
Press the mixture into the bottom of a spring-form pan.
With an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Add condensed milk, eggs and salt.
Beat thoroughly and add lemon juice.
Pour the mixture into the pan and bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool at room temperature and refrigerate.
Spread the sour cream over the cheesecake and garnish with fruit.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crumble cake
directions: Mix ingredients together like pie dough.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble 2/3 of mixture in pan.
Pat down lightly.
Top with one can cherry or any other pie filling.
Crumble remaining dough on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: spicy peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish or 3-quart shallow casserole.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat butter or margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar in mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add dry ingredients and beat at low speed until well combined. Spread batter evenly in pan.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Combine eggs, butter, flour, baking powder, soda, allspice, cinnamon, ground cloves and sugar together.
Add alternately with pinto beans.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place 5 cups cabbage.
Mix ground meat, rice, salt, garlic powder, sour cream and onion in bowl.
Spread on top of cabbage.
Spread 5 more cups of cabbage on top of meat mixture.
Put 1 can undiluted tomato soup on top of cabbage and 1/2 cup ketchup on top of that.
Sprinkle shredded Colby cheese to cover entire casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add 1 egg at a time. Cream and add sour cream, then flour. Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese with flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Cut baking potatoes into long quartered wedges.
Toss with cheese mixture and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, until crispy on outside but tender on inside.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour and cocoa until well combined.
Form into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 20 minutes.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out any shape cookie and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes and remove. Cool completely on wire rack (approximately 15 minutes).
Use pastry brush and coat each cookie with melted chocolate, then drizzle white chocolate.
Must stand 15 minutes or until chocolate is set.

title: fried cheese meltaways
directions: Heat oil (2 inches) in deep fat fryer to 375°.
Beat 1 cup baking mix, the milk and egg with hand beater until smooth.
Coat cheese cubes lightly with baking mix.
Insert a round wooden pick in each cheese cube; dip into batter, covering cheese completely. Fry several cubes at a time, turning carefully, until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes; drain on paper towels.
Makes about 45 appetizers.

title: carrot king cake
directions: In a mixer, blend beaten eggs with oil.
Add to mixture with buttermilk.
Add vanilla by hand.
Blend in the pineapple, coconut, carrots, nuts and flour.
Pour into floured and well-greased pans (use three 9-inch pans).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Lay brisket on heavy foil in a baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 4 to 6 hours.
It's easy and it's delicious.

title: prime rib roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt
and
coarse ground pepper and put into a 14-inch Dutch
oven.
Combine
1/2 can broth, apple juice and garlic juice and pour
into
the
oven.
Roast for 2 1/2 hours with 12 coals on the
bottom
and
coals on top. Check after 1 hour to make
sure	roast
is
moist
enough; if necessary add the rest of the beef broth.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cube (about 8 slices).
Set aside. Beat eggs.
Add sugar, margarine and milk.
Stir in pineapple and bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Melt chocolate squares over low heat.
Add sugar and oil.
One at a time, beat in eggs.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate chips.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Combine the dry ingredients with the chocolate mixture.
Chill for 2 hours.
Form the dough into 1-inch balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheets.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Drop by tablespoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: brownie thing
directions: Divide brownie batter in half and pour into well-greased and floured pizza pans.
Bake.
Let ice cream soften.
Spread evenly on one brownie layer.
Place other layer on top.
Place back in freezer.
Cut and dribble chocolate syrup on pieces.

title: cold sesame noodles
directions: Cook linguini according to directions (firm). Pour into colander and rinse with cold water; drain well. In large bowl, mix watercress, sesame oil, soy sauce, garlic and pepper.

Add drained noodles and toss to mix. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 24 hours to 3 days. In a steamer basket, steam snow peas or thaw if using frozen; drain. Add to noodles and toss before serving. Makes 8 cups or 12 servings.

title: yeast pancakes
directions: Heat water and milk to almost boiling in large bowl.
(I do this in the microwave.)
Sprinkle yeast on top of hot liquid.
Let sit 5 minutes; stir gently.
Add egg (I run hot water on it to warm it up).
Beat.
Add Bisquick; beat well.
Let bowl sit for 30 minutes in a warm place.
Mixture will look lumpy and bubbly. Pour in hot oiled skillet and fix like other pancakes.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes(crock-pot recipes)
directions: Wrap
precooked ham in foil.
Place in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 12 hours.
If desired, sprinkle ham with liquid smoke before wrapping in foil.

title: baked pizza sandwich
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir half of pizza sauce and the oregano into meat.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix the Bisquick, egg and milk.
Measure 3/4 of batter into greased pan.
Pour remaining sauce over batter; spread evenly.
Layer slices of cheese, the meat mixture, mushroom soup, remaining cheese slices and batter on top.
Spread with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken artichoke dish
directions: *Mix 1 cup white and 1 cup brown rice.
Cook with chicken bouillon and parsley flakes and 4 1/2 cups water.

title: mexican hash
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly in a microwave-safe bowl.
Add can of chili, cheese, salsa, and green onion.
Cook in microwave 2-4 minutes, until everything is hot and melted.

title: praline cookies
directions: Place crackers on an ungreased cookie sheet with the lines in crackers all in the same direction.
Heat butter and sugar to boiling.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes.
Add pecans.
Pour over crackers. Spread to cover.
Bake 10 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Cut crackers in half while still hot.
Remove from pan before completely cold.

title: watergate salad
directions: Chill in refrigerator to set.

title: green chili soup
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in skillet.
In a large stock pot, add beans, tomatoes, carrots and garlic.
Fill pot about three-fourths full of water and add bouillon cubes.
Cook for about 1 hour, then add potatoes and ground meat mixture.
Continue to cook over low heat, adding cumin according to taste.
Add chillies and salt and pepper and continue cooking until done. Great with cornbread.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer about 20 minutes.
Makes 2 quarts.
Double recipe for 1 gallon.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sherbet.
Let thicken slightly.
Add mandarin oranges, pineapple, bananas and nuts. Refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli puffs
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soup (undiluted), cheese, milk, mayonnaise and egg together.
Pour over broccoli.
(Separate broccoli slightly while pouring to allow mixture into broccoli.)
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: granny's green tomato chutney
directions: Mince tomatoes, apples, onions and raisins.
Mix together with all the ingredients and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: potato-pork chop casserole
directions: Trim fat from chops and brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Slice potatoes and season with a little salt and pepper.
Mix dry onion soup mix with mushroom soup and the water.
Mix well and pour into large casserole dish.
Add potato slices.
Place pork chops on top of potatoes and bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are tender.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine melted butter, dry yellow cake mix and eggs. Mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Top with crushed crackers and butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry dressing
directions: Place strawberries in a small bowl; stir in corn syrup, mashing berries slightly with a fork.
Add mayonnaise, stirring until well blended.
Chill about 1 hour to develop flavor and color.
Serve with fruit salad.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Let stand for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Then microwave for 1 minute on High.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Drain oranges.
Combine pineapple juice, pudding mix and orange drink mix (will be thick). Combine fruit and dressing.
Sliced bananas may be added.

title: shrimp and corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Drain all but several tablespoons bacon fat from pan.
With remaining fat, saute chopped onions and celery until clear.
Add garlic
and chicken broth.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil in chicken broth and sauteed vegetables until tender.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool and crumble.
Prepare chocolate mousse according to directions, omitting chilling.
Place half of brownies in bottom of a 3-quart trifle dish and top with half of mousse, crushed candy bars and whipped topping.
Repeat layers, ending with whipped topping.
Garnish.
Chill at least 8 hours.

title: basil tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours, then let stand out to room temperature.

title: nut and chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to mixture; add vanilla, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Turn into two square cake pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
While still hot, sprinkle remaining nuts and chips on the cakes.
Cut into squares and remove from pans when cool.

title: eggnog
directions: In a very large bowl, mix each ingredient until frothy.
Add each ingredient one at a time.
Chill.

title: butter ball dumplings
directions: Blend eggs and butter.
Gradually add flour, salt and cheese. Beat hard.
Drop by tip of teaspoon into boiling chicken broth. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: just like snickers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well. Spread mixture in an 8-inch square pan.
Cover and freeze at least 3 hours.
Yield:
16 servings.
One serving = 1 starch, 1 fat. Fat:
5.0 g. Calories:

title: three bean salad
directions: In large bowl, stir sugar, vinegar and oil together until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store, covered, in the refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake as directions
on
package
in
a 13 x 9-inch pan. While cake is baking, combine cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk. While cake
is
hot from oven, punch full of holes with fork. Spoon
milk/cream mixture over hot cake.
(This mixture will seem like
a
lot, but spooning slowly, it will seep into cake.) Cool, then
frost
with
Cool
Whip
and sprinkle with coconut.

title: fruit punch(yellow)
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.
Remove from freezer and let thaw at least 3 hours before serving.
Add 1 quart of ginger ale.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Mix together well and cook over low to medium heat until thickened.
Pour into one deep pie crust or two regular crusts. Top with meringue.
Enjoy!

title: spoon hamburgers
directions: Mix all together and cook 40 minutes slowly in skillet.
Toast buns and put mixture in buns as you serve burgers.
Makes 10 hamburgers.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until well mixed.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: spaghetti with mushrooms
directions: Simmer very slowly for at least one hour the onions and garlic in olive oil.
While onions cook, wash and soak dried mushrooms for 1 hour.
Combine ingredients and simmer slowly for another 1 to 2 hours.

title: pear crunch
directions: Mix all
of this well. Crumble on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts, mix well. Fold in nuts. Make into small balls and place on cookie sheet, 2-inches apart. Bake 8-10 minutes in 350 degree oven. Makes 6 to 6 1/2 dozen.

title: apple enchilada dessert
directions: Preheat oven 350°. Spoon fruit evenly onto all tortillas, sprinkle with cinnamon. Roll up tortillas and place seam side down on lightly greased baking pan. Bring margarine, sugars, and water to boil in a medium saucepan. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly for about 3 minutes. Pour sauce evenly over tortillas, sprinkle with extra cinnamon on top if desired. Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped okra
directions: Combine all ingredients except buttered crumbs.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top. Bake in a greased casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 generous servings.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Blend sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Pur in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: florida fish fillets with cream cheese stuffing
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs, cream cheese, onions, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spread on fish fillets.
Roll fish around stuffing.
Wrap 2 slices bacon around each fillet; secure with a wooden pick.
Place fish rolls in a well-greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry ham
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and wine.
Pour over ham. Bake ham at 325° for 2 to 3 hours. Baste every 20 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls out with fingers on cookie sheet and bake until golden brown.
